title: blueberry crunch
directions: Layer the following in an 8 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish: pineapple, blueberries, cake mix and chopped pecans.
Pour melted margarine over layered ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: country ham bone soup
directions: Break ham bone into 2 or 3 pieces.
Place in large soup kettle.
Add water; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bones; remove meat from bones.
Chop meat; return to broth.
Add carrot, celery and onion; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables. Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add macaroni; season with salt and pepper.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended. Bake in three 8-inch round cake pans that are greased and floured for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese, creaming until well blended. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Shape dough into 8 balls; wrap each in plastic wrap, and chill at least 2 hours.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, sugar and baking powder in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix; pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over oats. Stir. Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Grease and flour cake pan.
Mix together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat together butter and sugars in a large bowl until smooth, light and fluffy. Stir in eggs and vanilla. Add oats and mix well. Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Use the following frosting recipe.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rosenberry eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat half of the sugar with egg whites.
Blend egg yolks with other half of sugar.
Blend milk and egg yolks. Beat whipping cream to soft peaks.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Add vanilla and egg whites last.
Put a little nutmeg on top.
Enjoy!

title: golden applesauce
directions: Combine apple juice and jelly in a small saucepan and heat slowly until jelly melts.
Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of apple juice and stir into the hot juice.
Stir constantly as mixture thickens.
If it is too thick, add a little more apple juice.
Mixture should have the consistency of heavy syrup.
Serve with baked fowl.

title: tamale bites
directions: Combine cornbread, 1/2 cup enchilada sauce and salt.
Add beef.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow pan. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: jello cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make Jell-O by directions.
Pour over cake.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
When firm, top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until it becomes stringy.
Add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts become brown, about 30 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda last.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet and cool.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Bone and chop chicken or turkey into small pieces and mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: potatoes casserole
directions: Melt butter. Put half of butter in the bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups corn flake crumbs.
Pour the other half of butter on top of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cake(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Blend well on medium speed with mixer.
Flour chocolate chips before gently folding into cake mixture.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy; add coloring and eggs one at a time.
Beat 1 minute after addition of each egg.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa together 3 times; add alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in vinegar; fold into batter.
Pour batter into three 9-inch pans which have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 26 to 28 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell peppers in margarine.
Cook egg noodles in broth of chicken.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: egg rolls
directions: In a large skillet or wok, combine oil, cabbage, chicken and water chestnuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook on high heat until mixture bubbles, then turn heat on low and add soy sauce.
Cook for 5 minutes; drain and cool.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients; press down gently.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Make jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water and 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour 1/2 jello mixture in dish.
Let it set.
When chilled, spread sour cream over gelatin.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream. Let set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, milk, sugar and cocoa for 2 minutes, big boiling. Mix all together.
Spoon out onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Place 4 scoops (about 1/2 cup each) of ice cream in a small pan; freeze for 1 hour or until firm.
In small mixing bowl, stir together egg and vanilla.
In pie plate, stir cereal and cinnamon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4.
Roll these in cinnamon and sugar mix. Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Cover with brown sugar, pats of butter and cinnamon.
Make another layer and repeat, usually makes about 3 layers.
Sprinkle nuts on top of each layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan and cook until this forms a hard ball in cold water.
Turn off burner and add milk. Stir briskly.
Turn burner on and cook until this forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans. Stir until ready to spread in rolls and cut.

title: potatoes with corn flakes topping
directions: Put hash browns, 1/2-inch deep, on bottom of pan.
Brown onion in butter.
When that is brown, add cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix in onion, then pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and corn flakes on top of cheese.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box for layer cake.
Add pistachio pudding to cake mixture, blend thoroughly and bake as directed. Let cool before frosting.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and dates in a cold lightly buttered skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and rind.
Blend in cereal. Drop level tablespoons into coconut.
Shape into balls, coating with coconut.
Chill.
Makes 32 to 36 cookies.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with Wrights barbecue smoke.
Salt and pepper. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1/2 hour for each pound of ribs. Add sauce.
Simmer at 200° to 250° for 45 minutes.
Sauce is for 4 1/2 pounds of ribs.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hot and mild sausage and onions in skillet over medium heat. Drain excess fat.
Cut cheese into small cubes and add to sausage mixture, stirring well.
Spread over bread and bake 10 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl, then beat into the creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut and cereal.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets, leaving 2-inches between cookies. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until browned as preferred.
Let the cookies cool 1 minute on the sheets before removing to racks to cool.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add a little milk, some flour and 2 eggs at a time.
Beat well, then continue to add milk, flour and 2 more eggs until all ingredients have been added.
Beat well and bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: waffles supreme
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt butter and cool. Beat egg yolks until thick. Add sugar and milk; beat well. Add flour mixture, beating well. Add melted butter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake until golden brown.

title: tomato stack-ups
directions: Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch thick slices and sprinkle with salt.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of the cheese.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine remaining cheese and onion with broccoli.
Place tomato slices on baking sheet.
Spoon the broccoli mixture on tomatoes and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Broil 7 to 8 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Serves 6.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix together cream cheese, dressing mix and onions or chives. Spread cream cheese mixture on tortillas.
Sprinkle with last 3 ingredients.
Roll in jelly roll style and then in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Slice crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine margarine, corn bread mix and eggs.
Fold in onion, cottage cheese and raw broccoli (flowerets only).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place butter on cookie sheet.
Heat until melted.
Slice potatoes.
Combine Parmesan, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add potatoes and shake or toss to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour until tender, turning once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix sauce ingredients together; add cooked and drained broccoli.
Pour into baking dish and top with grated cheese and crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bacon potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add sour cream, Blue cheese, milk, butter and salt to mashed potatoes.
Beat with beater until fluffy.
Put in baking dish in 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon before serving.
Serves 4.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Let tomatoes stand in salt water overnight.
Cook all 1/2 hour and seal.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and spread on the muffins.
Freeze for 30 minutes before broiling.
Cut into fourths.
Broil until puffy and golden brown.

title: apple-pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package.
Add crushed pineapple and shredded apples.
Stir and pour into mold or fruit dish.
Chill until set.

title: crab-broccoli mornay
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender; drain.
Heat in saucepan butter and flour.
In a separate pan, boil milk and heavy cream. Add this all at once to the other pan.
Stir until thickened over low heat.
Stir in Cheddar cheese until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sherry.
Remove from heat.
Cut broccoli in small chunks.
Alternate layers of broccoli and crabmeat in baking dish. Pour sauce over all.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or just until cheese sauce bubbles and bread crumbs brown slightly.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together your milk and 2 packages Dream Whip until it is nice and fluffy.
Put in drained pineapple and cherry filling. Stir together well.
Put in long dish.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together. Can be made ahead of time and kept in the refrigerator.
(You may add a can of garbanzo beans for 1 can of yellow beans.)

title: delicious corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together very good; pour into greased baking pan. Put Crisco on top, if desired. Have oven hot, 450°, when you put your bread in it. Cook until brown on bottom and top.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cut off fresh corn. Combine above ingredients and heat on stove until oleo is melted. Cook 3 minutes. Refrigerate until cold. Put in freezer bags or boxes. When ready to cook, just make sure corn is heated through.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix as usual.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen.

title: turkey orzo
directions: Heat oil in skillet; crumble turkey about 5 minutes.
Stir in onion, garlic, thyme, pepper, oregano and cinnamon.
Saute until onion is softened.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook orzo in water al dente (according to package directions); drain. Stir orzo into turkey mixture and heat through.
Top with cheese; cover and cook just until cheese is softened.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Microwave butter in 2-quart casserole on High until melted. Stir in flour, chives, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes or until thickened, stirring every other minute.
Mix in potatoes. Cover.
Microwave on High 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix onion, pimento, bell pepper, mayonnaise, soup and cheese in bowl and mix.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Crush Ritz crackers; put on top.
Save a little cheese and sprinkle on top, also.

title: susie's tea cakes
directions: Make a mound of flour and pour a small amount of mixture on the flour.
Work until the mixture and flour have a consistency of cookie dough.
Pat out and cut cookies.
Repeat until you have used all the mixture.
Add flour as needed.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes until done at 375°.

title: goulash soup(servings: 6)
directions: Fry onions in hot fat until transparent.
Add green peppers and tomato paste. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add lean beef cubes and remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
(Add cubed potatoes, if you like and simmer until potatoes are done.)
Best when reheated and served the second day.

title: turkey divan
directions: Spray a large baking dish with vegetable spray and lay in it the parboiled broccoli.
Cover with the turkey slices.
Dribble melted butter over turkey.
Stir together chicken soup and sour cream.
Spread mixture over turkey; sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips and cheese. Turn into 11 x 7 x 1-inch baking dish. Top with potato chips and cheese that have been combined. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Serve immediately. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fish chowder
directions: Peel and slice carrots, onions and celery.
Saute them in margarine in a large pot (about 5 minutes).
Add the potatoes, chicken broth, V-8 juice, thyme, parsley and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: honey popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn and set aside.
Combine sugar, honey and salt in small saucepan.
Heat and stir to dissolve sugar.
Boil to the hard-ball stage.
Add the margarine and vanilla.
Pour the syrup over the popcorn and stir.
Butter your hands and shape into balls, then wrap in wax paper.

title: mississippi tea cakes
directions: Add baking soda to sour milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board and cut out into different shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. They may appear not quite done.
However, do not overbake!
Roll in powdered sugar after you remove from oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches) or line with paper baking cups.
Beat milk, oil and egg.
Stir in flour and sugar all at once, just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fold in blueberries.
Divide batter among muffin cups.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Form small balls and chill.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured pan or loaf pan. Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: easy red beans
directions: Brown sausage, add red beans, cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water. Cook until thoroughly heated, about 20 minutes.

title: my family sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Season chop meat with salt and pepper.
In a pot, put in sliced onion with a little water and saute until soft.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In a medium bowl, stir cream cheese and peppermint flavor until well blended.
Place cream cheese on a large piece of waxed paper.
Gradually work in powdered sugar with your hands until mixture holds together.
Add 3 to 4 drops of food color and work in until evenly tinted.
Make small balls, roll in colored or granulated sugar and flatten with a fork.
Let dry at room temperature.
Store loosely covered in the refrigerator.
Makes 4 to 7 dozen.

title: donna's strawberry stuff
directions: In large bowl mix pudding according to directions on box.
In another bowl mix cream cheese, sugar and egg until smooth.
Add to pudding mixture.
Add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Mix well.

title: frozen cake roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Slowly add sugar, beating until creamy.
Add flavoring, beat.
Mix flour and baking powder together and gradually add to sugar mixture.
Beat only until smooth.
Whip egg whites with salt until stiff but not dry.
Fold in flour.
Spread dough evenly in a heavy greased jelly roll pan lined with greased freezer paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Loosen and invert on clean towel sprinkled with powdered sugar, then roll like jelly roll leaving in towel as rolled until cool.
Unroll and fill with Baker's Icing and freeze.

title: stained glass gingerbread stars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare gingerbread mix according to box directions for cookies. Form dough into 2 balls.
Roll rolling pin in flour and roll dough approximately 1/8-inch thick onto parchment paper.
Using star shaped cookie cutter, cut a circle in center of each cookie. Place one candy in each center.
Place parchment paper with cookies on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes. Candy will melt and give stained glass effect.
Let cookie cool on parchment paper 5 minutes before removing. Yields 24 cookies.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until well blended.
Roll small amount of dough.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes great stars, bells and Christmas trees.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Mix in baking dish and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
This recipe may be halved and baked for 1 hour at 325°.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan and cook for 5 minutes after boiling. Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Put in buttered 9 x 9-inch dish.

title: jellied applesauce
directions: Cook candies in water over medium heat until melted.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in this liquid.
Add applesauce.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well.
Add sour cream and soda; beat well.
Add flour and blend. Add beaten egg whites* and flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes in a 300° oven.
Let set 10 minutes, then turn upside-down to cool.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients; put in casserole.
Add 2 cups boiling water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Last 15 minutes, add 1/3 cup soy sauce and can of chow mein noodles.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix in oven-safe pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased one-quart casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and one tablespoon melted margarine, sprinkle over corn.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes (4 servings).
May fold 1/2 cup shredded natural Cheddar cheese into the sauce mix.

title: pineapple pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add lemon juice. Pour into pie crust shells. Chill.

title: spicy chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and simmer until tender.
Remove chicken from broth. Add vegetables and parsley flakes.
Simmer until tender.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli as package label directs for 10 minutes only.
Cook rice, adding bouillon cube to water.
When cooked, toss rice with parsley.
Spread rice over bottom of greased casserole. Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Mix light cream with broccoli, then pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake 25 minutes or until cheese is brown.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce 30 minutes.
Dip chicken pieces in barbecue sauce, then roll in crushed barbecue potato chips. Place on microwave-safe meat rack; cover with waxed paper. Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 7 minutes per pound.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Crumble in margarine as you would for pie dough.
Moisten with beaten egg to which the milk has been added.
If too dry, add a little more milk.
Press lightly into a cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes. Serve warm with sliced berries, peaches or any desired fruit and milk.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Mix fruit, sugar and juice.
Pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, until light brown on top.

title: squash pie
directions: Combine squash, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes, or until knife inserted in filling comes out clean. Cool; serve warm or cool.

title: poppy seed fruit sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Chill; serve over fresh fruit.

title: strawberry-fig jam
directions: Wash and peel figs.
Mash and mix with other ingredients.
Let set for one hour.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. Makes 2 pints and 4 ounces.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Cook in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Add onion, pepper and garlic; cook about 4 minutes, stirring.
Drain tomatoes, reserve liquid.
Add chicken broth to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add liquid to skillet, bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and tomatoes. Cover, remove from heat, let stand until all liquid is absorbed (5 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: In large bowl, stir together the first 8 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and soup; toss with turkey mixture.
Turn into greased casserole dish and sprinkle top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: world's easiest chicken recipe
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Pour undiluted soup over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, then spread on bottom of 10 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch pan, greased.
Blend together all ingredients, then pour over top of cake mixture; spread around. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add 1/2 cup sugar, pinch of salt, 4 tablespoons oleo (melted), 2 cups bread crumbs (soaked in milk 10 minutes). Soak raisins in hot water 15 or 20 minutes.
After adding ingredients, add lemon drops and stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add the remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oven baked rice
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms or water chestnuts in butter.
Combine and bring almost to a boil the bouillon and water.
Combine vegetables and broth; pour over uncooked rice in casserole.
Submerge rice completely.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Add broth during baking if necessary.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, put milk, oleo and sugar.
Stir until dissolved. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add tidbits and coconut, then add nuts and peanut butter.
Add enough oats and stir until good and stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and flatten with fork. Cool.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour.
Mix salt, flour, milk, oil and egg white, then beat until smooth.
Add water to make a medium-thin batter.

title: cloud-light pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, lightly.
Will be bubbly and foamy.
Bake on well greased griddle.
Yields:
2 to 3 servings.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef; add salt, pepper and onion.
Cook until beef is done, then add beans, soup and water.
Add chili and vinegar, cook about 15 minutes.
You may add more chili powder.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large sauce pan over low heat. Add

and stir until completely melted. Remove from heat. Add rice krispies cereal. Stir until well coated. Using battered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: red, white and blue bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix in hot water and juices.
Add egg and shortening, then fold in berries (cranberries should be coarsely chopped).
Put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mary's sugar cookies (cut-outs)
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll out.
Use cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: caldillo
directions: Brown first four ingredients in small amount of oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Cook over low heat until tender, 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with rolled, buttered, hot tortillas.

title: open line casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Add soup and cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Place in casserole.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°. Add French fried onion rings; bake 10 minutes more.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: squash casserole #2
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish; top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Place 1/4 stick margarine in small pieces over cracker crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, use whole graham crackers to place on bottom.
Pour half the pudding mixture in, then another layer of graham crackers and remaining pudding on top.
Top with graham crackers and pour icing over.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: In large mixing
bowl,	mix
cereals
and
add	boiling water. Add buttermilk, sugar, eggs and oil.
Stir into cereal mixture very lightly.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate bavarian pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; cool.
Sprinkle gelatin onto 1 cup of milk in a medium saucepan; allow to stand for 2 minutes.
Combine sugar and cocoa; add to mixture in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; add butter and stir until melted.
Blend in 2/3 cup milk and vanilla. Cool; chill until mixture begins to set, stirring occasionally. Whip the cream until stiff peaks form; carefully fold into chocolate mixture, blending well.
Pour into pie shell; chill until set.
Prepare Strawberry Whipped Cream.
Pipe in a decorative design and top with reserved frozen or fresh strawberries.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix well.
Spread in 11 x 15-inch greased jelly roll pan. Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1 minute; remove from heat and add 2 cups strawberries. Pour into prepared pie shell.

title: making tracks pasta
directions: Cut chicken into strips as to stir-fry.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Add oil to skillet, add chicken and cook until done, stirring often.
When done, add vegetables and Italian dressing, stir and cook until vegetables are done. Serve over the cooked spaghetti.

title: aloha banana bread(from texarkana)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, bananas and orange rind. Blend thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add alternately with milk and flavoring, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° in a shallow, greased pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Blend together everything except cream cheese and 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.
Shape ball and frost with cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Can put chopped parsley on top.
Refrigerate covered with foil or Saran Wrap.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with 1 cup of milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in 1 cup of cookies and rocks.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with cookies.
Freeze 4 hours.
Garnish with gummy worms or candy.
Store in freezer.
Delicious for summer!

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil the zucchini and onions together for 5 minutes.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Put half of the mixture in a large baking dish. Combine squash, soup, sour cream and carrots.
Pour over stuffing. Top with remaining stuffing. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches and cream delight
directions: Drain peaches (sliced) and place in 9-inch square baking dish. Combine oats, flour, sugar and butter into crumbly mixture. Spread over peaches.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with vanilla ice cream when ready to serve.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine
eggs,
milk,	crushed
crackers,
onion,
1/2 teaspoon dry
mustard
and	pepper.
Add ground ham and ground pork; mix well.
Shape
into an 8 x 4-inch loaf and place in a 13 x 9x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa over low heat.
Beat eggs and sugar and add to chocolate mixture.
To this, add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased pan and cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli stir-fry
directions: Wash broccoli; cut off broccoli flowerets.
Peel broccoli stems; slice stems 1/4-inch thick.
Heat oil in a large skillet or wok; stir-fry broccoli 5 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch in a small bowl; add honey, ginger and Tabasco sauce.
Pour mixture over broccoli; cook until sauce thickens slightly.
Stir in almonds.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease or Pam a 9 x 13 pan. Dump applesauce evenly over the bottom of the pan.

title: easy home style potato salad
directions: Heat potatoes and 3 cups water to boiling in 2 1/2-quart saucepan; reduce heat. cover and simmer until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse under running cold water; drain.
Mix 1 cup water and the sauce mix in saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cool.
Mix potatoes, celery, onions and eggs.
Fold in sauce mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled at least 2 hours.
Garnish with paprika, if desired.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then add dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and rest of ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet, spreading far apart.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in groups of 4 on cookie sheet.
Combine milk and syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring to prevent scorching. Cook until caramel colored and thick (230° for 20 to 30 minutes) or to soft ball stage.
Spoon caramel onto nuts while still hot. Top with 2 squares of chocolate bar on each Turtle and swirl when chocolate has melted.

title: pork chops mexicana
directions: Brown chops in lard or drippings.
Arrange in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and season with salt.
Sprinkle rice around chops. Combine taco mix, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over chops and rice.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours (depending on thickness of chops).
Remove from oven 10 minutes before done.
Sprinkle with cheese and arrange green pepper slices over surface of chops and rice.
Cover and continue baking.

title: chicken vermicelli salad
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones. Dice for salad. Break pasta in fourths and cook until done. Chop celery and bell pepper. Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: swiss hash browns
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Break hash browns and place in pan. Grate Swiss cheese over potatoes.
Mix.
Pour whipping cream evenly over potatoes.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, granulated sugar and margarine. Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coleslaw 2
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots.
Add drained pineapple, reserving juice.
Make dressing by adding sweetener and small amount of pineapple juice to the yogurt to suit your taste.
Add yogurt mixture to slaw, combining well and refrigerate before serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: tuna bacon macaroni bowl
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions, except use 1/2 cup milk instead of 1/4 cup. Add mayonnaise, tuna, bacon, eggs, pickle relish and mustard.
Chill several hours.
If desired, serve in lettuce lined bowl. Garnish with additional bacon. Serves 6.

title: santa fe soup
directions: You will need a crock-pot. (I cook in larger pan and then transfer to crock-pot; faster.)

title: baked tomatoes and cheese
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of tomatoes in baking dish; cover with bread crumbs and 1/2 of the cheese.
Dot with butter.
Add remaining tomatoes and top with cheese formed into a circle.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: slush punch
directions: Simmer sugar and 1 cup water until sugar is dissolved.
Add all the juices and freeze.
Take out 2 hours before serving.
Mix 1 quart sour or Squirt with 1 pint of the slush mixture.

title: midnight spice cookies
directions: Into a bowl, sift flour with soda, cinnamon, ginger, allspice, cloves and salt.
In large bowl, cream butter with brown sugar until light.
Beat in eggs, molasses and Worcestershire sauce. Slowly beat in flour mixture.
Place in refrigerator for 10 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: junkyard salad
directions: Mix all together and put into the freezer.
When ready to serve, cut into squares.

title: strawberry rouse
directions: Whip softened cream cheese with sugar on high speed.
In a separate bowl, whip heavy cream with 2 teaspoons vanilla until stiff.
Put cream cheese mix into heavy cream mix and whip on low speed until blended.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Keeps several weeks in blender.

title: taunia's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: little pizzas
directions: Mix all together and place 10 biscuits in muffin tins.
Press dough in tins and make hole in center and put hamburger mixture in.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven fried pecan chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch dish. Dredge chicken in pecan mixture.
Place chicken in oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, cover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Press margarine and graham cracker crumbs into a pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: wassail(christmas drink)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Garnish with orange stars.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese; add oranges and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, water, jello, sugar and pinch of salt until it thickens.
Add drained strawberries.
Let cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together, except Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes or longer.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix together sugar and Karo syrup in large pan.
Boil this for 2 minutes. Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add corn flakes and drop onto wax paper until set.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large (4-quart) microwave-safe bowl, microwave on High for 20 minutes the first 3 ingredients, stirring every 5 minutes. Stir in chocolate morsels and marshmallow cream.
Mix until smooth.
Add walnuts and vanilla extract.
Pour into large, greased baking pan or cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in a large bowl. Add Pet milk. Empty can, then fill with water and add this to bread. Add sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and pineapple. Blend well and add to casserole dish that has heated and melted oleo. Cook in a 375° oven until thick and pudding is slightly brown around edges and on top.

title: trifle
directions: Crumble some of cake in bottom of bowl, then add a layer of fruit, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and butter together.
Bring to boiling point.
Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Add milk and butter to egg mixture. Add flavoring and baking powder.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with your favorite veggies.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: pinto beans
directions: Boil beans on slow fire until tender.
Fry meat; remove from heat.
Fry onions, garlic and bell peppers until medium brown. Add meat and seasoning to beans.
Stir well.
Add rest of ingredients; cook 4 to 5 hours, or until beans begin to break up.

title: amber onions
directions: Mix all ingredients except the onions in a saucepan. Heat until dissolved. Pour over onions. Bake at 350°. Bake for 1/2 hour covered, remove cover and bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: scott's famous pennsylvania barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add all other ingredients.
Mix and heat, but do not bring to a boil. Brush onto meat.
Delicious on chicken and all other kinds of meat. Use as a marinade also. Store in refrigerator and reheat before using.

title: lazy gravy
directions: To cook a roast all day in a crock-pot, add cream of mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix.
The result is a tasty gravy with little work.

title: kathy's peach cobbler
directions: Let peaches and sugar boil until done; set aside to cool.
Melt margarine and cool.

title: authentic italian wedding sweets
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time and beat them in. Add melted Crisco and anise flavoring.
Form by hand into shapes, i.e., finger sized rolls, etc.
Bake at 400° until light brown. Cool only slightly.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Bring chicken to boil in water.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Remove and cool.
Pour stock into measuring cup to make 2 cups and refrigerate.
Skim any fat from top of stock when cooled.
Debone chicken.
Cut chicken into chunks.
Place all ingredients in pot and cover, bring to boil, turning heat down immediately.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes or until sauce has thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Lightly grease casserole with oleo.
Pour 1/4 of cracker crumbs in bottom of dish.
Pour mixed chicken, soup and sour cream over crumbs.
Melt oleo and mix with crushed crackers.
Spoon over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: passover stuffing(for chicken)
directions: Saute onions in fat.
Mix all ingredients and stuff chicken. Bake as usual.

title: better way rolls
directions: Pour warm water into mixing bowl; add yeast.
Let stand a few minutes; stir to dissolve and add half of flour.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Use mixer or mix by hand until smooth; 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add rest of flour and stir by hand until flour disappears (it will take 1 1/2 to 2 minutes).
Scrape batter from sides of bowl.
Cover bowl with wax paper.
Let mixture rise in warm place until doubled in size (about 30 minutes).
Grease large muffin cups.
Fill 1/2 full with mixture and let rise in warm place until double in size (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 350°. Makes approximately 1 1/2 dozen large rolls or can be made in loaves.

title: katie's homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Take strawberries out of freezer an hour before you make the ice cream.
Pour one cup of strawberries into a 1-quart plastic freezer container.
Pour in the sugar.
Pour in the cream and stir well with a spoon.
Close the container and put it in the freezer. Freeze until firm.

title: bread and onion custard with cheese casserole("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mince onion and saute in margarine.
Remove crusts from bread and cut in 1-inch squares.
Butter a baking dish and place beaten eggs in milk and pour over the other ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour or until custard sets.

title: sage beer bread
directions: In a bowl, mix the flour, sugar and sage.
Add the beer and mix with a spoon until blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out dry.
Cool on a wire rack.
Butter can be rubbed on the top while still warm.

title: applesauce-date cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add eggs, sugar, oleo and 1 cup hot applesauce.
Beat at low speed just until combined, then at medium speed for 2 minutes, then add remaining applesauce, dates and nuts; beat 1 minute.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: gumbo
directions: Take home, give to wife and say "I want some Gumbo."

title: john wayne casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Put chilies on bottom of the pan.
Beat 4 egg whites in a bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat 4 egg yolks, small can of evaporated milk, 2 tablespoons flour and salt and pepper.
Mix the yolk mixture in with the beaten egg whites.
Then mix in the 4 packages of cheeses.
Slice tomatoes on top after pouring above mixture over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in large bowl.
Set in oven with towel over it overnight.
Punch down; knead and divide in 3 parts. Put in 3 oiled pans.
Let rise 8 hours.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Brush with butter when hot.
Cool and cut.
Wrap good for freezer.

title: swiss bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald 2 cups of milk.
Add the salt, sugar and the soft butter.
Stir as it cools so sugar will not settle on the bottom of the pan.
Add yeast.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour. Add the slightly beaten eggs to mixture.
Add more flour; knead it. Let rise in bowl for 1 hour.
Punch down; let rise for 1/2 hour, then braid it and let the bread rise.
Smaller loaves are easier to bake.
Small loaves take 20 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: creamy fruit and rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mint, in a large bowl.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Mint sprig is just for decoration.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; set aside. Cream together butter and shortening; add cream cheese and sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually beat in flour mix.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough 1/8-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost as desired. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: german sands
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Use hands to shape dough into shapes the size of dates.
Put all on a large, ungreased cookie sheet. Refrigerate 1/2 hour or overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes or until barely tanned.
Turn off oven.
Remove 8 to 12 cookies at a time. Replace cookie sheet in oven.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar. Keep in closed container.

title: "great" chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, dry milk, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Beat eggs, oil, butter and vanilla in separate bowl.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture only until just blended.
Quickly fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen large muffins.

title: snickers dessert
directions: Mix pudding and the skim milk.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Combine Tang, pudding and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Pour over fruit.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
May use fresh fruits and nuts.

title: pork and beans hamburger
directions: Brown onion, garlic and hamburger until meat loses its pinkness.
Drain off oil and add pork and beans and seasoning. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: grandmother's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix next 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl and pour into dish of melted butter. Pour fruit over the mixture. Sprinkle top with cinnamon. Do not stir mixture once in baking dish. Bake in a 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add all ingredients together in a boiler.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat.

title: apple-anna bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch loaf pan.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas, apples and vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour.

title: bake beans for 75
directions: Put beans in roaster, add onions, diced (as many as you like). Add brown sugar, mix well.
Put in bacon (cut in small pieces). Add small amount of barbecue sauce.
Last, put in ketchup and stir well (put as much ketchup in to make the mixture red).
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: nanny hall's sweet potato pies(makes 4 pies)
directions: Combine potatoes with margarine and mix until smooth.
Add sugar, milk, eggs, extract and nutmeg.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 450° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Can freeze mix alone before cooking or freeze pies.)

title: perfect peanut butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside. Cream together peanut butter and milk, then add to dry ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
This is best when it's a day old.

title: pea casserole
directions: Cook the celery, onion and green pepper in the margarine until soft.
Combine the pimento, peas, soup and water chestnuts. Combine all ingredients.
Put in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6 or more.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook beef in 1/2 cup water until it is dry.
Add soup, catsup and chili powder.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
This is good on dry beans also.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan. Stirring constantly, bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for at least 2 full minutes, or until candy thermometer registers soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat, add butter and stir to melt. Add vanilla after candy cools, about 5 minutes; then add nuts. Pour into buttered platter.
When cool and firm, cut into squares.

title: chicken oriental casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cut in pieces.
Mix soup and mayonnaise with chicken.
Add rest of the ingredients, but only half of the potato chips.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; sprinkle with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Good served with rice.

title: mushroom-brown rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3 quart or 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour; uncover, and bake 15 more minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
8 servings.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water; save 1/4 cup of water.
Cream raisins. Combine shortening, sugar and eggs; mix.
Dissolve soda in raisin water; add to mixture.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves; add raisins.
Mix.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: great spice blend for diabetics
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use on meat and poultry.
Even my doctor thinks this is great.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; remove skin and fat.
Debone and chop chicken into cubes.
Layer meat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Melt oleo and mix with poppy seed and cracker crumbs.
Spread over top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs and set aside egg whites.
Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk and butter; cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell and beat egg whites with a pinch of cream of tartar and 5 tablespoons of sugar.
Put on pie and let brown.
This makes one pie.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry ground beef; drain. Place in deep pan. Add onions, Italian seasoning, Tabasco sauce, tomatoes, enchilada sauce and tomato sauce. Stir and simmer, stirring at intervals, for 4 to 6 hours. Cook lasagna noodles. Alternate layers of noodles, cheese and sauce in baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and grind pears.
Mix ingredients and cook over medium heat.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Cook unti thick. Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix sour cream and yogurt.
Pour over vegetables and cheese. Do not stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir once before serving.

title: fancy fondue
directions: Beat cranberry sauce in saucepan.
Add cornstarch, cinnamon and ground cloves; blend well.
Add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add franks (cut into bite size pieces); cook until franks are done.

title: favorite oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine pancake mix, salt, paprika, onion salt, garlic powder and pepper in shallow bowl. Beat milk and eggs in small bowl. Rinse chicken and pat dry. Dip in milk mixture; coat with pancake mixture. Place, skin side down, on rack in shallow baking pan. Brush with melted butter. Turn; brush with butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is cooked through.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice, and set aside.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take out of pan to cool, reserving broth.
On low heat, add rice, bell pepper, onion, celery and butter to broth.
Let cook until done.
Remove from heat and add broccoli, diced chicken, salt, pepper, garlic salt, soup and milk. Stir gently and place in large casserole dish.
Place sliced Velveeta on top and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: very best cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream; beat until smooth.
Add eggs, butter, sugar and the remaining ingredients.
Beat until very smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Turn off, but leave cake in oven for 2 hours without opening door. Remove from oven.
Leave in pan until cold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: california rice
directions: Mix soup with rice.
Spread 1/2 of the rice mixture on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Evenly layer 1 can of jalapeno peppers, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 can of olives.
Repeat process; rice, peppers, cheese and olives.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, corn meal and vanilla together.
Cut margarine up in mixture (do not melt margarine).
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Saute the celery, onion, almonds and water chestnuts in a little margarine.
Combine rice, soup and mayonnaise and mix well. Stir in celery, water chestnuts, onion, almonds, cheese, chicken, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil box of Mueller's elbows until noodles are well done. Drain; cut up block of sharp Cheddar cheese.
Mix sharp Cheddar cheese, butter, pepper, salt, 1/2 package of Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 package of Cheddar cheese and two cups of whole milk.
Preheat oven to 350°.
After well mixed, pour into a square baking dish. Put the rest of the package of Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese on top (sprinkle).
Put in oven and let bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: caraway cheese sticks
directions: Place flour, butter and salt in a bowl and mix until crumbly. Add the Cheddar cheese, caraway seed, mustard, paprika, cayenne pepper and red pepper sauce to the bowl and mix together.
Add the milk and knead until the mixture forms a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: roast wild duck
directions: Wake husband at 4:00 a.m., load his hunting jacket pocket with bird shot, shotgun shells.
Get out his shotgun (optional).
Serve him coffee (breakfast, optional).
Walk to front door, give friendly, kiss good-bye (optional).
Keep it friendly or hunt may be postponed.
Wait (who knows how long).
Important!
Husband plucks duck, you must keep hands clean of all feathers.
Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Place duck in piece of foil (large enough to loosely wrap) and fold over at top.
Pinch on ends.
Place duck, breast down; cut apple and onion in quarters.
Stuff inside duck, squeeze margarine all over this side of duck.
Apply seasoning, turn duck over, apply margarine and seasoning and slice the lemon into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Place 2 slices of lemon on breast of duck.
Enclose in foil.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Place in oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with rice or dressing.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat, together.
Pour sauce over meat and let sit in refrigerator for a day or two.
Place meat on cookie sheet in oven at 140° for about 4 hours or until dry.

title: black walnut custard
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, molasses and water.
Add flour and nuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sweet or red hot barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer slowly 20 minutes, stirring often to keep from scorching.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and onion dip.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Cook hamburg and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix, following directions on back of package.
Layer hamburg over cream cheese layer.
Spread lettuce, tomato and onion.
Top with cheese pieces.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Any taco chips may be used for dipping.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In large bowl combine Eagle Brand and water.
Mix well.
Add pudding mix and beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Using a 2-quart trifle bowl, spoon 2 cups mixture into bowl.
Top with half the cake cubes, 1 cup of the strawberries and 1/4 cup of preserves. Repeat using half of the remaining pudding mix, all of the remaining cake cubes, sliced strawberries and preserves.
Top with remaining pudding.
Garnish with strawberries and almonds.
Chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Unroll crescent dough.
Lay flat on cookie sheet or pizza pan. Seal all edges.
Bake as directed on package.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy on low with electric mixer.
After crust is cool, spread mixture on crust evenly.
Slice canned, frozen or fresh fruit of your choice. Arrange in pretty pattern on top of cheese mixture.

title: baked ziti with sausage
directions: Remove meat from casing and break apart and brown meat; remove and saute chopped green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook and drain pasta.
In Dutch oven, mix pasta sausage, sauce and chilies.
Put into large baking dish.
Cover with more Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.
(Makes enough for a small army.)

title: marinated turkey
directions: Place turkey in browning bag in shallow roasting pan.
Combine parsley, oil, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over turkey.
Seal bag.
Cut slits in top and bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: crunch cake
directions: Mix and pat on the bottom and edges of 2 greased loaf pans.

title: upside down strawberry shortcake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows evenly into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish; set aside.
Combine strawberries and gelatin and set aside. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Pour batter over marshmallow.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter and bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares and garnish with fresh strawberries and whipped cream.

title: wilted cabbage with cheese
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until wilted.
Drain.
Place in buttered casserole in alternate layers with cheese and soup.
Top with crushed chips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans.
Cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
In a frypan, use oil to cover the bottom of pan.
Heat it.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add parsley.
When it is sauteed and still hot, bring the beans to a boil and pour garlic/onion mixture into beans. Cook on low for 2 hours.
May also cook ham hock in beans.
Serve over rice.

title: christmas eve punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and almond extract.
Mix well.
Freeze until mixture is slushy.
Before serving, add 7-Up.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Shake before using.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg, mashed bananas and milk.
Fold in sifted flour and soda. Grease and flour a loaf pan and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan when cooled.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion; add meat and seasonings.
Cook until meat is done.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into casserole dish. Mash potatoes. Add milk, eggs and seasonings.
Spoon into mounds on meat.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Roll cheese ball in 1 cup of pecans.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, olives, sour cream, salsa and onion in a bowl.
Alternate layers of mixture with tortillas and cheese, ending with cheese.
May be doubled.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: "clay" fun
directions: Mix together.
Add additional applesauce or cinnamon to get consistency desired (dry/doughy).
Roll out.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Make hole on top with pencil.
(Shape will shrink some.) Bake at 150° for 1 hour or until dry.
Turn over halfway through. Can be painted.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, cornstarch and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add package of jello; stir.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberries (cut in half).
Pour into baked pie shells.
Chill before serving.
Serve with whipped topping, optional.

title: beef and bean nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and
drain.
Add
taco seasoning mix, following package directions for
preparation.
Add
chili	to mixture.
Heat Cheez Whiz
in microwave following label directions.
On a plate or platter,
place tortilla chips, top with meat mixture, then cheese.
Serve with salsa.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice garlic into bowl.
Add salt.
Mash these together and add the juice of the lime.
Carefully peel and chop the avocados.
Save 1 or 2 of the seeds.
Mix avocados into the lime and garlic mixture.
May use potato masher, but do not make "mashy."
Mix in the sour cream.
Finely dice the tomato and add to the mixture.
To prevent salad from becoming dark, put 1 or 2 seeds into salad as you let it chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shoepeg salad
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Cool.
Mix last 7 ingredients and drain well.
Combine and refrigerate.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Line oblong baking dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour in cherry pie filling.
Melt butter and sugar together.
Mix in cream cheese.
Mix Dream Whip with milk according to directions on package and whip.
Combine with cheese mixture and spread over pie filling.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over top.

title: scalloped corn jiffy mix
directions: Mix all ingredients except Jiffy mix.
Mix well, then add dry corn bread mix.
Stir.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Chop or tear lettuce in bite-size pieces on bottom of dish (about 3/4-inch).
Cover lettuce with peas; cover peas with mayonnaise.
Chop onion on top of mayonnaise, then sprinkle the bacon over the onion.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: k.c. baked beans
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish; top evenly with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix following package directions.
Shape into ball.
Wrap in wax paper; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to hot (400°).
Divide pastry in half.
Roll out one half on lightly floured surface into a 12-inch circle.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: crisp cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers, leaving some skin for color.
Slice cucumbers thin.
In a deep bowl, combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add cucumber slices and cover.
Refrigerate for 6 hours. Drain to serve.

title: baked creamed potatoes
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until soft.
Add pimento, flour and milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Place shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients, form into one inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheet until golden brown. Makes 6 dozen. These may also be frozen uncooked. For a firmer texture add an extra 3 cups of baking biscuit mix and an extra 2 cups of shredded cheese to ingredients listed above.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: You will also need a paper bag.

title: batters buns
directions: Combine chopped hot dogs, cheese and relish.
Fill hot dog buns with mixture.
Wrap individually in foil.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden brown.
Drain well.
Soak bread in 1/2 cup milk.
Combine meat with fried onions, soaked bread, eggs, salt and pepper.
Roll into 1-inch balls and fry in butter or oil until evenly brown.
Shake pan often to keep balls round.
Remove meatballs; drain well.
Add flour to the grease and blend well.
Add bouillon and milk or cream; stir until sauce is thickened and smooth.
Add sherry and additional seasonings, if necessary.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sour cream nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Combine flour and other dry ingredients together. Blend flour mixture into shortening mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in nuts and drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Mix 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; sprinkle on top of cookies. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1/2-inch strips.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet.
Stir-fry chicken 3 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken broth, salt, pepper and ginger.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a separate skillet and stir-fry vegetables for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with water and stir into chicken. Add cooked vegetables and serve over rice.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top middle of each square with topping.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra firmly into hot jars leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Put a garlic bud and 1/2 a pepper in each jar. Combine water, vinegar, salt and dill seed and bring to boil. Pour hot liquid over okra leaving 1/4-inch head space. Remove air bubbles. Adjust caps. Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath. Yield: about 4 pints.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter and bubble cheese in large frying pan.
Add 4 to 5 teaspoons heavy cream and fresh pepper.
Drain fettucine, dump in and coat quickly.
Add more cream if it appears dry.
Heap on platter and top with grated cheese.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
You may use as topping, bread or cornflake crumbs. Bake for 45 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: fruit sour cream pie
directions: Spoon sour cream into bowl; add sugar, vanilla and a few drops coloring.
After cooling, place in fridge.
Before serving, add Cool Whip.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into halves and shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Put in a greased tube pan, adding nuts and raisins if desired. Melt butter with brown sugar and add vanilla.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert pan immediately after removing from oven.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish, layer broccoli, chicken, bread cubes and cheese.
Combine gravy, milk and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix with 1 stick butter.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until looks solid.
Let cool.

title: dad's apricot pie
directions: Cut up apricots.
Put in saucepan, adding sugar, lemon juice and water.
More sugar can be added to taste.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until mixture thickens.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with fluted crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is browned slightly.
Cool before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, and Eagle Brand milk.
Add mayonnaise and salt.
Mix all together and store in refrigerator.
The longer it is refrigerated, the better it is.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: cornbread salad(christmas salad)
directions: Mix cornbread mix as directions show.
Bake, then crumble bread. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate until you serve.

title: jiffy peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches.
Pour into baking dish or pan.
Mix dry cake mix and syrup together; pour over peaches and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: clyde's chili
directions: Cook hamburger, green pepper and onion together.
Add chili mix.
In a separate large pot, cook spaghetti.
When spaghetti is done, drain.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
If too thick, add more tomato juice or water.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in a electric skillet.
Cook on low all day or until tender (at least 2 hours).

title: cranberry apricot sauce
directions: Combine orange juice and thinly sliced apricots. Cover. Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake as directed.
Whip together cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Add fruit as listed.
Sprinkle with coconut, then Cool Whip and top with nuts.

title: red cabbage slaw
directions: Crush bacon over salad between paper towels.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Add green pepper rings before serving.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes, counting when mixture has reached a rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla. Beat well until blended. Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well and pour in an 8 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: mexi-casserole
directions: Saute peppers, onions and celery.
Add meat and brown.
Drain. Add Ro-Tel and cheese soup.
Line baking dish with Doritos.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until warm.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 425° prior to baking.
Combine flour, salt, eggs and liquid in blender at least one hour prior to baking. Flash blend occasionally to mix well.
Prepare 6 muffin tin with knife point or knob of fat in each cup.
Immediately prior to baking, place tin in oven and heat fat (less than 5 minutes; watch or you will have a kitchen full of smoke!)
Remove and fill each cup with flour/egg/milk mixture.
Place in hot oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve at once; in true Yorkshire tradition, as a starter with gravy.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil together sugar, white syrup and cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually pour syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Beat until mixture starts to set and has a dull look.

title: vegetable-meat stew
directions: Fry meat and salt and pepper to taste.
Drain grease.
Put meat and all vegetables in a layer in a cooking pot.
Pour herb tomato sauce in and then fill with water.
Salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Cook on low heat.
Feeds many people and stores easily.

title: french onion dip
directions: Combine sour cream and onion; blend together.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken and rice curry
directions: Boil chicken pieces.
When tender, drain and debone.
Boil rice in chicken broth. Saute onion, green pepper or celery in butter in skillet. When chicken is tender and boiled down, add chicken and remaining ingredients.

title: garden spanish rice
directions: Fry hamburger and drain well.
Add rice, juice, onion, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in chopped green pepper, cucumber and tomato. Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: ksra(algerian bread)
directions: In a bowl, dissolve sugar in 1 cup of lukewarm water.
Sir in the yeast until it dissolves.
Set
mixture in a warm place for about 5 minutes until bubbly and nearly doubled in volume.

title: mini-biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients. Drop by teaspoon in mini-muffin pan. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg in mug.
Add rum and boiling water.
Stir until blended.
Add cinnamon stick stirrer.
Serve immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift flour and add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour or line with wax paper 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° until golden brown and tests done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on pizza pan or cookie sheet and cook until light brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix squash with all ingredients, except milk; beat until mixed, then add milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate which has been lined with pastry.
Place into hot oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
This makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit. Mix together in a large bowl. Chill and serve.

title: rhubarb iced tea
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 hour.
Strain the liquid.
Add sugar to taste and serve iced with sprig of mint.

title: connecticut beef dinner
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add beef, onion and water; cook to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour meat mixture into greased baking pan (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Arrange potatoes over meat.
Stir together soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cornflakes.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar, white sugar and oleo until chunky. Take out 1 cup mixture and set aside for topping.
To rest of mixture, add egg, sour milk, salt, soda and vanilla; mix lightly. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of turkey soup
directions: In a bowl, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
In a pot, combine butter and flour.
Blend in bouillon mixture, vegetables, turkey and seasonings.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes. Blend in milk and egg yolk; cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Garnish with chopped chives.
Serve.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening well.
Sift flour and sugar 3 times.
Add gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix soda and hot water in cup and add to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk mixture to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions, using a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding with milk.
Put candy bars in freezer until hard, then smash in Ziploc bag with a hammer (or use Heath Sensations).

title: poppy seed filling
directions: Bring milk to boiling point and add poppy seed.
Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring carefully, until milk is absorbed.
Add sugar or honey.
Beat egg thoroughly.
Mix 1 tablespoon of hot poppy seed with egg and pour into cooked poppy seed.
Stir until thick.
Add vanilla.
Must be thoroughly cooked before using.

title: cherry jello supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cherry pie filling.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate to partially set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Beat together salad dressing and cream cheese.
Gradually add lemon Jell-O while continuing to beat.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Pour carefully over partially set cherry layer.
Top with chopped walnuts.
Chill until set.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
In another bowl, beat eggs, milk and oil.
Add to corn mixture and stir in peppers, corn, cheese and onions.
Pour into 2 well oiled baking pans (9 x 11-inches) and bake in 425° oven for 25 minutes or until it tests done.

title: baked salmon
directions: Peel skin off of salmon fillet.
Place salmon in a baking dish. Poke holes in the salmon and place bits of garlic inside.
Sprinkle remainder of garlic over salmon.
Place potato slices and chopped onion around salmon.
Pour olive oil and lemon juice onto salmon, potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with a lid or tight foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until fish is flaky.
Salt to taste and serve with French Salad (see Salads for recipe) and French Bread.

title: spinach bisegnano
directions: Combine spinach, cottage cheese, bread crumbs, eggs, mushrooms and green pepper.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Spread sour cream over top.
Spread 1/2 of spaghetti sauce over top.
Spread 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat another layer of sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle with basil and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
On the bottom of the pan, put cooked, diced chicken.
(You can use 4 to 5 chicken breasts or a whole chicken.)
Mix part of a package of frozen vegetables with the chicken.
Next, mix one can of cream of celery soup with 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.

title: easy italian wedding soup(stracchiatella)
directions: Saute onion in oil until transparent.
Use a 3-quart saucepan. Add wine and bring it to a boil.
Add broth, spinach and meatballs.
Bring to a boil again and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and simmer 10 minutes more.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chrusciki(crispy pies)
directions: Beat until lemon colored the egg yolks and salt.
Add sour cream.
Mix.
Add sour cream and rum, whiskey or sweet wine.
Add and mix in gently the flour.
Knead until blistered, using a small amount of flour only when dough becomes sticky.
Roll thin.
Cut into strips about 4 x 2-inches.
Slit in the middle and pull ends through to make "bow-ties".
Fry in deep fat, 350° to 375°.
Drain on brown paper.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups cake mix, flour and yeast in a bowl; add warm water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in eggs.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over batter; set aside.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Stir in pecan halves. Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 225°.
Mix up every 15 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook salt pork or bacon.
Add onions and cook about 10 minutes.
Add milk and potatoes.
Boil 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add corn; season to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: julie's pineapple delight
directions: Mix together pineapple and juice and vanilla pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
It's so easy and good.
Be creative, add whatever you want.

title: stuffed crescent rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients (except rolls) in large bowl and set aside.
Open crescent rolls making sure to keep a "square" shape by softly pressing along slit marks to keep dough together.
(You should get 4 "squares" per package.)
