Spoon 1/3 to 1/2 cup of chicken mixture into center of dough and fold up sides, pinching together to seal shut.
When finished, brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put meat in pot.
Add soup and dry onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375 ° for about 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a square casserole pan.
Place one slice of cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Mix wine, water and soup together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle croutons on top. Re-cover and bake an additional 15 to 30 minutes longer.

title: cherry surprise
directions: *One-half
cup
mixed in ingredients, 1/2 cup sprinkled over top.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water, then mix in pie filling and pineapple.
Place in loaf pan or dish and chill.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and nuts.
Spread over jello mix. Refrigerate.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage; drain.
Mix all ingredients together, leaving bread and margarine for top.
Top with bread crumbs and pour melted margarine over bread.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bread has browned.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook in saucepan until smooth (medium heat).
Cook fettucini until desired consistency and drain.
Ladle Alfredo sauce onto drained fettucini.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli first in water.
Put cooked broccoli in ungreased dish.
Beat soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle on cheese.
Mix Bisquick and melted margarine; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Parboil, peel and cube potatoes.
Red skin potatoes don't require peeling.
Mix mustard, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl, then toss with dressing from small bowl.
You may wish to add extra mayonnaise to taste or to moisten immediately before serving.
Serves 12.

title: dirt
directions: Crush cookies.
Remove 1 cup cookies and set aside.
Add remaining cookies to butter, cream cheese and sugar; mix well. Add milk, pudding and Cool Whip to cookie mixture.
Mix well. Line large clay flower pot or small individual flower pots with Saran Wrap.
Fill with cookie mixture.
Cover with dry cookie crumbs.
Place an artificial stem of flowers in pot.

title: ham stack appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese, horseradish, mayonnaise and salt.
Mix and spread evenly on all but 1 slice of ham. Stack slices on top of each other, topping with plain slice.
Wrap and chill.
Before serving, cut into bite size pieces.
Serves 24.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender. Don't overcook.
Drain when cool.
Alternate layers of bell pepper rings, onion slices and carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: helen's cabbage to freeze
directions: Bring vinegar, water and sugar to boil and cool.
Mix cabbage and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add to cabbage the pepper, carrots and celery salt.
Pour vinegar, sugar mixture over vegetables.
Mix and let stand one hour.
Package and freeze.

title: grilled flank steak sandwiches
directions: Add 1/2 garlic and 2 onions to wine.
Marinate steak for 2 to 3 hours, turning.
Slice bread on diagonal.
Melt butter; add thyme and garlic (2 teaspoons).
Spread on inside of bread; wrap in foil.
Grill steak to desired doneness.
Slice steak in thin strips at an angle.
Heat bread in oven while steak is cooking; heat until crusty on outside.
Stuff bread with steak strips; slice in 2-inch pieces.
Serve with salad.

title: hillbilly goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Meanwhile start macaroni.
Use a large pot for this you will add to it later. Once macaroni is done, drain and place back into pot.
When the hamburger is done, drain and add it to the macaroni.
Add all other ingredients except for cheese, stir until mixed well. Reheat and sprinkle with cheese.

title: pancit
directions: Saute garlic in cooking oil.
Add onions, pork (or chicken), carrot and cabbage; season with soy sauce.
Add broth; simmer.
Mix in rice sticks (Bijon); season with salt to taste and MSG (optional).
Garnish with Chinese sausage and scallions.
May also serve with hard-boiled egg, cut up or scrambled egg, cut in strips.

title: green beans oriental
directions: Heat beans in own juice for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine bean sprouts, water chestnuts and cheese.
Make alternate layers of beans and cheese mixture in casserole dish.
Blend flour, salt and Worcestershire sauce in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over vegetables, lifting with fork to coat all vegetables.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine, add almonds and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: curried tilapia
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium high heat.
Add lemon juice, curry powder, soy sauce and garlic.
Mix well and heat until bubbly.
Lay filets in skillet and saut 2 minutes. Carefully turn over filets and cook another 2 minutes or until fish flakes. Serve extra sauce over filets.

title: sugar cookies(soft)
directions: Cream together oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt to first mixture.
Roll out.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Can frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with bottom pastry.
Flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add all other ingredients except noodles and cheeses.
Simmer about 10 minutes while cooking noodles according to directions on bag.
Pour noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over noodles and stir together with hamburg mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar and pizza cheeses on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite salad-caesar
directions: In a very large wooden salad bowl, pour olive oil.
Crush cloves of fresh garlic with back of spoon in the olive oil.
Mash anchovies with the garlic and oil, prepared mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Break coddled eggs (boil water; turn off and then set eggs in it for 1 minute.) into mixture in bowl and beat with whisk.
Add juice from lemon and beat again.
When ready to serve, throw in the romaine.
Sprinkle toasted croutons and Parmesan cheese over the lettuce and toss well.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Measure
into
sifter flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and
cocoa.
Sift
together and add Crisco, 3/4 cup milk and vanilla.
Mix
until
all flour is used.
Add eggs and 1/4 cup more milk.	Bake in 2 (8-inch) layer pans at 350° about 35 minutes.
Be sure to use Baker's cocoa.

title: loco moco
directions: Mix together ground beef, 1 egg, 1/2 of the envelope of soup mix, 2-3 tablespoons shoyu, pepper, garlic powder, and bread slices.
Shape into 4 patties.
Cook patties in a large skillet until browned and cooked through (or however you like).
Remove patties from skillet and set aside, leaving any drippings in the skillet.
Add onion to skillet and cook in drippings until onion is soft (about 5 minutes).
Combine flour with remaining dry soup mix and add to skillet.
Stir in 3 cups water, and bring to a boil.

Add bouillon cubes and simmer about 10 minutes or until desired thickness, stirring constantly so the bottom doesn't burn. While gravy is simmering, fry remaining 4 eggs in another skillet "sunny-side up" or "over easy" style and set aside.
In 4 bowls, put a generous amount of cooked white rice.
Place one hamburger patty on top of rice.
Place one fried egg on top of each hamburger patty.
Cover rice, hamburger, egg combination generously with brown gravy.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Brown chops and arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup, water and thyme.
Heat, then add parsley, sour cream and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Pour over chops. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle on rest of the onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix together.
Pour over cheapest ham you can find.
Bake at 225° for 7 hours, basting every hour.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Take cookie sheet and place graham crackers side by side (about 46 crackers).
Sprinkle nuts on top of crackers.
You may also use some coconut if desired.
Put margarine and sugar in pan; bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers and nuts. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
When cool, store in ziploc bag.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of cake pan; add your cans of chili.
Add diced olives; on top, add shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese on top is melted.
This dip is great for chili dogs or put over chips.
Basically with this dip you can spice it up with peppers or add anything you like.

title: tuna pie (mock chicken)
directions: Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover with biscuit dough (follows).
Bake in 450° oven for about 20 minutes until nicely browned.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream oil, oleo and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Beat with mixer.
Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Blend well, then stir in zucchini. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, flavoring, cocoa and milk.
Put on stove and boil 2 minutes and 3 seconds.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by wax paper.
Let cool.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over brisket in a glass baking pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered with foil, in marinade at 275° for 5 hours.

title: triple chocolate squares
directions: Line bottom and sides of an 8-inch square pan with foil.
Beat 1/2 cup almond paste, semi-sweet chocolate and 1/4 cup butter. Spread evenly in bottom of pan. Chill while making next layer.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in paper cups in muffin tins. Freeze. Serves 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat. Heat to boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours. Add beans, macaroni and water.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken soup and sour cream and onion (chopped fine).
Mix together and then add frozen potatoes.
Mix well again.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill for 1 hour. Take approximately 1 tablespoon of candy and roll in red sugar crystals; shape like strawberries. Put green sugar crystals on top for foliage. Keep refrigerated.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add fruit and nuts.
Beat eggs; add with vanilla.
Pour into fruit mixture and mix with hands.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes (9 x 13-inch pan for double recipe).
Use loaf pan for single recipe. Line pan with aluminum foil for easy removal.

title: fat-free cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake according to box instructions.

title: "home for christmas" vegetable soup
directions: You can add your favorite vegetables to or in place of any of the ingredients.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch square dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over the butter in the dish.
Spoon pie filling on batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: joslyn's jewels(breakfast)
directions: Toast Eggo.
Spread butter over Eggo.
Sprinkle powdered sugar, then cinnamon sugar.
Top with candied sprinkles.
Good with chocolate milk.

title: chicken curry
directions: Heat oil over high heat.
Brown chicken and set aside.
Pour off fat and add butter.
Add onions and garlic and saute for 5 minutes.
Add chilies, ginger and apples and cook 3 minutes until soft.
Mix in curry powder and cook about 1 minute.
Add coconut, cardamon and lemon grass and salt.
Bring to boil and simmer for one hour.
Serve on rice and top with lemon juice and cilantro.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, salt and vanilla with an electric mixer on high speed about 4 minutes or until thick. Gradually add the 3/4 cup granulated sugar; beat on medium speed for 4 to 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add the pancake mix; beat on low speed just until combined.
Spread batter in pan that's prepared.

Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden and cake springs back when lightly touched near center. Immediately loosen edges of cake from pan and turn cake out onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up towel and cake, jellyroll style, starting from one of the short sides.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Brown celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add soups and cheese spread.
Heat until warm on medium heat.
At the same time, prepare broccoli (without salt) and rice according to package directions.
Drain broccoli and rice.
Add to the other ingredients; pour into a casserole.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Put pieces in angel food pan sprayed with Pam or lightly greased. Bring butter, brown sugar and white sugar to a boil. Cook until thickened. Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: great american meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inch) in shallow loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow meat loaf to stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, pepper and onion; drain.
Mash.
Mix with egg, milk and seasoning.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, then sprinkle top with cheese and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: good pie crust every time
directions: Blend flour and shortening well.
Sprinkle with water.
Stir with fork until mixture holds together.
(Some brands of flour will require more water.)
Do not overmix.
Form into ball.
Let rest 5 minutes before rolling.

title: 5 egg coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add extracts and mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: sweet sour tidbits
directions: Roll meat into tiny balls. Combine sauce and jam.
Start cooking slowly. When boiling, add meat balls; simmer 40 minutes.

title: toffee or almond butter crunch
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar, Karo and water. Cook to 300°, stirring occasionally.
Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts.
Pour out onto slab or pan prepared with 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts and half of the chocolate; cool.
Cover with chocolate and last 1/2 cup nuts.
Or pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Coat with chocolate and nuts.
Invert on waxed paper and cover second side with chocolate and nuts.

title: hot chili and beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add packet with 1/2 cup water.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Stir until mixed.
Add chili powder, red pepper, jalapeno peppers, salt and pepper to your taste.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: pound cake(low-fat)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add to it 1 egg and beat, then 1 egg white at a time; beat.
Add flavorings.
Beat.
Add flour and baking powder and stir into batter with the buttermilk. Grease pound cake form and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: drum roll bars
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add egg and coffee, then dry ingredients.
Raisins and nuts are added last.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting while warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: For extra flavor and moisture add 1 teaspoon banana extract and 2 tablespoons applesauce.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange chicken pieces.
In small bowl, combine other ingredients.
Brush mixture on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: deluxe apple pie
directions: Mix together the apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Put into pie shell and dot with butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in casserole overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Take out, cover with crushed potato chips and slip back into oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Can use leftover turkey in place of chicken.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges to use to cook pudding until thickened.
Chill pudding; add fruit.
May be made the night before.
Slice bananas just before serving and add to fruit mixture.

title: french onion soup
directions: In covered large saucepan, cook onions in butter over low heat about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add consomme and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cover corned beef with water in a kettle.
Heat to boiling. Skim off foam.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, or until meat is tender. Wash cabbage; remove the heart.
Cut into quarters; shred or leave in wedges, if preferred.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: In food processor, blend first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Slowly add oil and blend.
Store in sealed jar in refrigerator.

title: cornbread souffle
directions: Mix together.
Spray dish.
Bake in long casserole, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinder cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix with melted margarine or butter and make into crust in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan, holding back 1/2 cup of cookie mixture.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine yogurt, milk and frozen lemonade.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together in pie crust and cook 45 minutes on 300°.

title: asian soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except snow peas and meat.
Bring to simmer 10 minutes.
Add snow peas and continue to simmer 2 minutes.
Add meat; allow to heat and serve.
You may add fresh mushrooms if desired.
Serves 4.

title: zesty italian mini loaves
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine ground beef, oats, 1/4 cup tomato sauce, egg, 1/4 cup sliced olives, 1 teaspoon onion and Italian seasoning; mix well.
Shape into four loaves; place in 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain off any fat.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese; heat.
Spoon sauce over meat loaves; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese. Serves 4.

title: turkey vegetable soup(good after thanksgiving)
directions: In a soup kettle, combine broth, potatoes, carrots, celery and onions; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add corn, beans, turkey, and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
14 servings (3 1/2 quarts).
Serving size:
1 cup.

title: green and white vegetable bake
directions: Melt margarine in a medium skillet until foam subsides.
Add cauliflower and broccoli stems, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots, onion, pepper and cauliflower and broccoli florets.
Cover and cook until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Add cheese, garlic, seasonings and vegetables.
Turn into a lightly greased deep 3-quart baking dish.
Place baking dish in a large shallow pan filled to 1-inch depth with boiling water.
Bake until knife inserted in center of casserole comes out clean, about 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: babe ruths
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Chill for a few minutes.
Shape into desired size and place on waxed paper.
Dip into the chocolate glaze.

title: eagle brand magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter, pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs and top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 26 bars of cookies.

title: bubble bread
directions: Line tube pan with rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar over rolls. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over brown sugar. Sprinkle butterscotch pudding and nuts over sugar mixture.
Pour melted butter over all and let rise 8-10 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Measure water into large warm mixing bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, corn oil, egg, salt and half of flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
When dough rises, punch it down occasionally.
Cut off amount needed and return remaining dough to refrigerator.
Dough may be kept for 3 or 4 days.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix with hands.
Make balls and brown in hot oil.
Place in baking dish.

title: lemon-ammonia cookies
directions: Purchase Baking Ammonia at a drug store.

title: chocolate almond coffee
directions: Place coffee and nutmeg in blender or food processor.
With processor running, add extracts.
Stop and scrape sides with spatula.
Process 10 seconds longer.
Place mix in a bowl and stir in almonds.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container. Yields enough for eight 6-ounce servings.

title: aunt evelyn kear's sugar cream pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add egg yolks and egg.
Mix , then add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake until set.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place a layer of chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix next 4 items; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over all. Mix butter (melted) and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and all is bubbly.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream all wet ingredients slowly then add dry ingredients mix well.
Bake at 350 -375 degrees for 10 -12 minutes.
Good for cookie cutters.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole.

title: wine drops
directions: Cream
the
first
6 ingredients together until smooth. Chop raisins fine.
Add raisins, flour and salt.
Blend until melted. Place cookies on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham strata(make ahead main dish)
directions: Cut 24 rounds of bread with cutter; set aside.
Fit scraps of bread in bottom of greased pan.
Place layer of cheese over bread, then layer of broccoli, then ham.
Arrange rounds on top of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over mixture. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 55 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat and add the graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over the top of mixture in pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Bring to a rolling boil light brown sugar and butter.
Boil 2 minutes and remove from fire.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Good!

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Whip egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until frothy. Slowly beat in 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until meringue is stiff and glossy.
Spread into a well-buttered and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes or until dry and crisp.

title: sweet-sour chicken breasts
directions: Bone chicken. Combine flour and garlic salt. Coat chicken with flour and cook in hot oil until brown. Add chicken broth. Cover and cook slowly 13 minutes. Drain pineapple and reserve syrup. Combine 1/4 cup reserved syrup with cornstarch, curry and ginger. Blend in soy sauce, catsup, vinegar and honey.
Pour over chicken and blend. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes longer. Add drained pineapple and pea pods.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Arrange chicken and sauce on serving platter. Sprinkle with green onions.

title: rita's dried tomato dip
directions: Steep tomatoes in warm water (1/2 to 1 hour) until soft. Drain.
In food processor, mince garlic.
Add tomatoes and cheese and blend.
Slowly add olive oil until desired consistency is reached.
Make night before serving.
Serve on crackers or toasted baguettes, etc.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Add
sugar
to	boiling
water;
bring to a boil again. Add remaining ingredients;
boil for 3 minutes.
Pour into an unbaked pie
shell;
top
with butter and cinnamon.
Top with another pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, garlic salt and salt. Pack mixture into 9-inch pie pan.
Spread tomato paste over pie, spread cheese and oregano over top of meat, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over on top of meat.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Rinse and pick over beans.
Place beans and 4 cups water in glass bowl and soak overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Boil 2 minutes, until thick and clear.
Add 1 package of strawberry Jell-O (dry).
Stir well until Jell-O is dissolved.
Pour over berries while hot.
Chill.

title: white chip cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and sift in medium bowl.
Beat in a large bowl the margarine, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil the cabbage leaves in salt water 5 to 8 minutes or until tender. Combine the next 8 ingredients.
Place equal portions in each leaf. Fold 2 opposite ends over and place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, seam side down.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage rolls and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vegetable-cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with hands; form into a rectangle on waxed paper.
(Rectangle should be the length of a loaf pan.) Place Cheddar cheese, onion and pepper in center of meat; roll sides up into a loaf and seal the ends.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: banana applesauce bread
directions: Take banana mix with sugar and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients with bananas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quiche for a crowd
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 X 13 pan for 50 - 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust.
Layer fruits on top, as desired.

title: easy chicken marengo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour with tarragon, salt and pepper. Dip chicken pieces in seasoned flour to coat on all sides. Heat butter and oil in large skillet; brown chicken pieces, a few at a time, until golden.
Remove to an ovenproof casserole.
Add wine to skillet and deglaze by scraping up brown particles from the bottom of the pan.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and garlic.
Stir to combine.
Pour sauce over chicken pieces and cover.
Place in oven and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white sauce mix
directions: Mix flour, dry milk, pepper and salt.
Cut in margarine until a coarse, mealy texture.
Store in a cool place until ready to use.
Makes 5 3/4 cups sauce to mix.

title: three minute cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder, milk and salt until all lumps are gone. Dump fruit on top, but don't stir it in.
Bake 1
hour at 350°.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix sugar, cooking oil and eggs together.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, pecans and sliced peaches.
Mix with mixer and peaches will mash up.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: honey mustard dip(for vegies, chicken, fish, salads)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Great for getting kids to eat vegies.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Divide into 8 (I usually divide into 4 rather large balls) parts and pat into rounds 1/2 inch thick on a cookie sheet.
Prick with a fork.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake about 30 minutes longer.
Cut into 8ths and return to oven until the edges are brown.
Store in airtight container.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with blueberries.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; good with white icing.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter, then add peanuts and drop on waxed paper until hard.

title: strawberry-banana delight
directions: Mix up jello and water.
Add other ingredients.
When jelled, frost with sour cream.

title: judy's chicken tortilla bake
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with strips of tortillas.
Mix together canned ingredients (no water) and spread on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil for first 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese with fork until smooth.
Gradually add remaining ingredients except for 1 cup of the nuts.
Shape into ball.
(It will be very moist.)
Roll in remaining cup of nuts and cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon loaf spread
directions: Whip all ingredients together and form into a log shape. Chill 24 hours or freeze 1 hour.
Roll chilled log in 3 tablespoons chopped parsley and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter. Beat until well blended. Add milk and confectioners' sugar. Beat well.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour into crust, cover with plastic wrap and place in freezer.

title: eagle brand magic lemon pie
directions: Put Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk, lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks into a mixing bowl.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Pour into chilled crumb crust or cooled pastry shell.

title: oven baked pork chops
directions: Mix soup, water and milk together.
Brown porks chops in small amount of shortening or oil; drain off.
Pour soup mixture over chops; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roast tips
directions: Put in crock-pot for 4 hours or bake in oven for 4 hours at 275°. It is very good.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs on all sides.
Melt fat in saucepan, add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until flavors are blended. Pour sauce over browned spareribs.
Cover tightly and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: baked chicken breasts in wine
directions: Note:
If desired, marinate and bake chicken in same greased dish.
Or marinate in double plastic bags in refrigerator overnight.
Let chicken come to room temperature before baking.

title: sauerkraut hot dish #2
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, drain.
Layer in 9 x 13 pan: hamburger and sauerkraut.
Top with egg noodles, then soups.
Add 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Then top with remaining 2 cups cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Heat iron skillet in oven a little with a bit of oil.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: seasoned potato spears
directions: Measure seasonings into a large dry bowl; mix thoroughly. Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice potatoes (no need to peel) into 6 (1-inch) spears.
Place spears in single layer on pizza pan; baste with melted butter.
Sprinkle with seasoning mix lightly.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until golden.
(Seal seasoning mix and use on meats, salads and vegetables.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 5 minutes at 350°. Let cool. Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Drain juice from strawberries and add enough water to make one cup. Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add to strawberries. Spread over Cool Whip and chill until firm.

title: opal's chess bars
directions: Melt
butter
and let cool.
Then mix butter with 1 egg and the
cake
mix.
Press
in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together
eggs and the confectioners sugar and cream cheese (softened).
Pour
over
top of first mixture and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook, tightly covered, on top of stove for 10 minutes at low temperature.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes more or until macaroni is tender.
Serve in casserole.

title: tomato lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, heat oil.
Add onion; cook, stirring frequently, until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Set aside.
In bowl, stir together the Ricotta cheese, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
In bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish, spread 3/4 cup tomato mixture.
Spread about 1/3 cup cheese filling on each noodle to within 1 inch of ends; roll up.
Place Roll-Ups, seam side down, in prepared dish; top with remaining tomatoes.
Cover; bake for 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese; continue baking until cheese melts.
Serves 4 (2 Roll-Ups each).

title: dilly-icious chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper.
Place skin side down in single layer on baking sheet.
Dot with shortening. Bake 1/2 hour in 400° oven.
Turn chicken; baste with combination of melted butter, water and dill.
Bake another 1/2 hour, basting 2 or 3 times.
Turn oven off and keep chicken in oven another 40 minutes to crisp.
Makes 6 servings.

title: adobo
directions: Place garlic in bottom of large heavy kettle (tight lid).
Put pork on top of garlic, then chicken.
Cover each piece of meat with sauce (no salt).
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Stir gently so sauce covers meat.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: elegant shrimp sauced fettuccine
directions: *You may use 1/2 shrimp and 1/2 scallops.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup to 170°.
Add peanuts and continue to cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Beat to a foam.
Pour into a well buttered cookie sheet; spread and sprinkle with salt.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Do not forget the salt.

title: granny smith's chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, apple and eggs in bowl. Add mayonnaise, barbecue sauce, salt and lemon pepper; mix gently. Serve with crackers. May use as sandwich filling. Yields 8 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss together and serve.

title: sharon's christmas cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Heat until your house smells like Christmas (on high for 3 hours or on low most of the day)!

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Bake on greased and floured sheet pan (10 x 15-inch) at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan, reserving 1/2 cup of mixture for topping. Gradually add milk, extract and food coloring to Kraft Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.
If desired, substitute 1/4 cup green creme de menthe for milk.
(Omit peppermint extract and coloring.)

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Melt butter and add to eggs.
Mix with mixer, then add flour and mix with hands.
Roll; let dry, then cut into strips.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add in order the graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and chopped walnuts.
Pour condensed milk over the layers.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients. Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool slightly (about 15 to 20 minutes) and remove from pan on cake plate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: "deluxe salmon cakes"
directions: Beat 1/2 cup mayonnaise, egg and mustard; add to salmon and other ingredients.
Make into cakes and refrigerate about 1 hour. Dip into cracker meal and fry in olive oil.

title: peach congeal salad
directions: Put Jell-O and crushed pineapple in boiler and let come to a boil.
Take off heat and let cool.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk and mix well.
Let congeal.

title: chunky baked beans
directions: Cut kielbasa into small chunks.
Put in a large frying pan. Fry on medium heat.
Chop onion and green pepper and add to meat. Fry about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add can of beans, mayonnaise, mustard and ketchup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir constantly. Cook until hot.

title: black-bottom banana bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Blend in the bananas. Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Divide batter in half. Add cocoa to half; spread into greased 9 x 13 pan. Spoon remaining batter on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: rocky road peanut butter squares
directions: Heat syrup and sugar to boiling in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Immediately remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Place cereal in large bowl. Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal, stirring until well coated.
Cool 2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows.
Press mixture in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Heat chocolate and shortening over low heat until melted; drizzle over squares.
Let stand until chocolate is set; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mash cheese well.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and flour.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in.
Bake in 350° oven until knife comes out clean.

title: cake and fruit kabobs
directions: You will need 6 (8-inch) bamboo skewers.

title: steak with tarragon wine sauce
directions: Heat a heavy, well-seasoned skillet over high heat.
Sprinkle salt over bottom. Place steaks in pan and sear 1 minute over high heat.
Turn steaks and reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, turning once for medium-rare.
Remove steaks from skillet and keep warm.
Increase heat to medium and sprinkle tarragon in skillet.
Add Worcestershire sauce and simmer until almost evaporated.
Stir in wine, turn heat to high and boil until reduced by half.
Add butter and swirl to melt.
Pour sauce over steaks.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine; add 1 tablespoon sugar and pretzels.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzel crust.
Top with pie filling of your choice.

title: dean hetler's lemon pot de creme
directions: Grate lemon peel and set aside.
Place jello in a bowl and stir in lemon juice until soft.
(Place bowl in pan of hot water and stir until dissolved.)
Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar, salt and lemon peel until thick and creamy.
Stir in jell, then fold in whipped cream.
Turn in pots or serving dishes and garnish with mint leaf.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill thoroughly.
Can be served in demi-tasse cups with demi-spoons.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, and vanilla until well blended. Blend dry ingredients; mix with creamed mixture and add nuts. Spread in a well-greased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: lori's vegetable soup
directions: In large pan on medium heat add V-8, celery soup, onion and butter.
Heat until butter melts, then add vegetables, salt, pepper and cook until vegetables are done; then add a pinch of baking soda and stir, then add milk to your desire.
Heat a couple of minutes and your soup is ready to eat.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat ingredients.
Put into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°, then 25 to 30 minutes at 325° until done.

title: ham and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Butter both sides of bread and cut in cubes.
Layer 1/2 of bread in the bottom of a 6 x 10-inch glass Pyrex sprayed with cooking spray.
Next, layer 1/2 of grated cheese.
Layer ham over bread and cheese.
Add layer remaining bread cubes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Mix milk, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to eggs and mix.
Pour mixture over cheese, bread and ham layers.
Let stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: roasted potato spears
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash potatoes and cut into shape and size of
pickle
spears.
Dry with a towel.
Coat potatoes with vegetable
oil
in
bowl.
Put on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole with ritz crackers
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix flour and water together.
Add to onion and cook until thick.
Add cut up cheese; stir until blended.
Add cooked, drained broccoli.
Add beaten eggs.
Pour into a casserole dish and cover with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart pot, start 3 quarts of water with 2 teaspoons shrimp boil liquid to boiling.
Add sausage and cook 5 minutes, boiling.
Add potatoes and cook 5 minutes, boiling.
Add corn and cook 3 minutes, boiling.
Add shrimp and cook at low boil for 4 minutes.
Dump into strainer, then onto a big sheet of freezer paper and everyone dig in.

title: beef pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes, except reduce water to 1 cup. Stir in egg; spread on bottom and sides of a well-greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes. Brown beef and celery (some like a little onion, too) in large skillet. Pour off liquid. Stir in water, tomato paste, sugar and salt. Bring to boil. Spoon into potato crust. Sprinkle with topping. Continue baking at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until top is brown.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Add barbecue sauce.
Place into oven at 350° for 1 hour or until tender and done.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers and onions.
Place in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with a layer of ice cubes and lay a terry towel over everything.
Let soak about 3 hours.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cook to a good boil egg yolks, pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar. Beat egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat well and fold into pineapple mixture after the gelatine has been added. Pour in crust and chill.

title: zucchini and kielbasa
directions: In a large skillet, saute the zucchini, onion and green pepper in oil until crisp and tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook until heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: boiled crawfish
directions: Fill large pot 1/3 to 1/2 full of water.
Add all ingredients except crawfish.
Bring to boil.
The aroma will knock your socks off, but seasoning must be strong to penetrate crawfish shells. Cook 10 pounds of crawfish at a time.
Add crawfish.
Cover and return to full boil.
Remove crawfish, peel and dip in a cocktail sauce.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slow for 2 1/2 hours.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and 7-Up, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into a large tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham and pork with remaining ingredients.
Shape into loaf. Place in a shallow roasting pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or 2 hours if topping is not used.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Line greased spring-form with ladyfingers; dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Whip cream; fold pineapple and gelatin into cream (cubes of jello folded in optional).
Pour in pan a layer of ladyfingers alternately with cream mixture.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: tuna almondine salad
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold water. Let stand 1 minute.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
With wire whip or rotary beater blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, curry powder, salt and garlic powder.
Fold in green onions, pimento, tuna and 1/2 cup almonds.
Turn into 5 1/2-cup greased mold or bowl. Chill until firm.

title: taco bake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except taco chips and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You may put crushed taco chips on top of casserole before serving or put taco chips on individual plates and spoon casserole on top of chips.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix all ingredients together, making sure sugar is dissolved. Pour into a quart jar with holes punched in the lid.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Starter is now ready to use.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Bring butter, eggs and sour cream to room temperature.	Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch tube pan or bundt pan and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until very smooth and creamy.	Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour three times.
Add baking soda to sour cream to sugar mixture, blending well, add all flavorings. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold gently into mixture.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler or microwave on Low. Place all other ingredients in heavy iron skillet.
Stir with wooden spoon over medium heat until mixture reaches hard crack (20 to 30 minutes).
Spread evenly in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Wait 3 minutes.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: california walnut pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour in saucepan.
Add corn syrup, butter and salt.
Warm over low heat just until butter is melted.
In large bowl, beat eggs with vanilla.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Turn into pie shell and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake on lower rack of oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until filling is set in center. Cool before cutting.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In 6 quart Dutch oven, cook sausage, celery, onion and garlic until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients, except pasta and zucchini.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add pasta and zucchini.
Simmer 20 more minutes, or until pasta is tender. Season to taste.
Serve with crusty Italian bread or breadsticks. Yields 6 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put pineapple, bananas and strawberries in blender and blend until slushy.
Mix all ingredients together and serve cold.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except margarine.
Pour into an oiled baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add vinegar and water and bring to boil. Simmer about 5 minutes until sauce is clear.
Add drained beets and stir well.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour.
Rewarm and add butter before serving.

title: rice crispy treets
directions: Get a bowl, then chalklite chips, then Rice Crispys, then butter, then marshmellows.
Stir it for a few minutes.
Put it in the oven for 30 minutes.
Let it set for 10 minutes and then you have Rice Crispy Treets.

title: mixed bag
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to a greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix uncooked sausage and Bisquick with hands.
Melt cheese and pour in sausage mixture.
Form balls and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° in ungreased pan.

title: cranberry apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Peel, core and slice apples. Place in 9 x 13-inch baker. Combine cranberry sauce, sugar and flour in bowl. Mix well, then pour over apples.

title: red and green bean salad
directions: In bowl, combine ingredients.
Dress with artichoke marinade and Italian dressing, as desired.
Chill 10 minutes.
Serve on a bed of lettuce, if desired.

title: very moist prune cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add other ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating very well.
Stir in flour, then flavorings; add 7-Up.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: colorful party punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to package. Chill all liquids. Mix equal parts of juice, ginger ale and Kool-Aid.

title: grilled ham steaks
directions: Mix marinade ingredients.
Baste ham slices at start of grilling and continue to baste as meat is turned.

title: peanut butter popcorn balls
directions: Combine raisins and popcorn in a large bowl.
Combine peanut butter, water and corn syrup in a saucepan and heat until boiling; stir constantly.
Lower heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour immediately over the popcorn.
Let cool a few minutes and form the popcorn into balls.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil or microwave chicken until done.
Fix Stove Top according to box directions.
Cube chicken and place in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Spoon out soup and cover chicken.
(You may need to add a little milk if too thick.)
Cover with Stove Top.
Bake in oven at 350° until top is crispy.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients well and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Dough:
Mix the cream cheese, 1 stick oleo and flour together and let stand 1 hour; refrigerate.

title: delicious roast beef
directions: Wash roast and pat
dry.
Using your hands and/or paper towels, grease roast
with
cooking
oil.
Then sprinkle roast with Italian seasoning.
Use your hands to pat seasoning so it will stick to roast.
Bake
uncovered
in
a foil-lined baking pan at 325° for 45
minutes per pound.
Slice thinly to serve. Good hot or cold.
Delicious for sandwiches.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sweetener; add eggs and extracts.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and baking soda; mix all ingredients well. Roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.
Carbohydrate 9.2 g, protein 1 g, fat 2.3 g, calories 78.
One cookie = 3/4 bread exchange, 3/4 fat exchange.

title: skillet fudge bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and cream.
Bring to boil in skillet or saucepan, stirring constantly.
Boil gently 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in whipped topping (Cool Whip). Layer whole crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add half the pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers and the rest of the mixture.
Top with a layer of crackers and cover top with chocolate icing.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until it forms a hard ball in cold water. Add butter and peanuts, stirring all the time.
Cook until the peanuts begin to pop and turn brown.
Have a 9 x 13-inch pan greased with butter. Add your vanilla and soda, stirring while it is forming.
Pour into pan.

title: jambalaya
directions: In an iron Dutch oven, brown onion in lard, then stir in flour.
Next the chopped tomatoes, shrimp and ham and let them cook while you stir carefully.
Add 2 cups boiling water and let simmer a while; wash the rice and add to the pot.
Stir once and cover.
Cook until done.

title: grandma bessie's pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer (or by hand).
Drop teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs (one at a time), vanilla and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Put berries in 1 cup flour. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: felicia's spiced tea
directions: Combine.
Mix 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of water, depending on how many you want to serve.

title: pea casserole
directions: Put peas in a casserole dish.
Chop up chestnuts, onions and pimentos.
Add soup and dressing mix.
Stir together and add grated cheese on top.

title: butter chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour gradually; beat in buttermilk, then vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until pie is golden brown.
Makes one (10-inch) pie.

title: potato kugel
directions: Coarsely grate the potatoes; squeeze out excess water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate onions; beat eggs.
Add potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and bread.
Mix well.
Oil a baking pan and put in oven for 5 minutes.
Pour the hot oil into batter, stirring a little, and then pour the batter into the hot pan.
(This makes the kugel crusty.)
Bake for 1 hour.

title: gourmet's delight
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a lightly buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle buttered crumbs over top. Bake, covered, at 325° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sunburst muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased miniature muffin tins.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Dip warm muffins into glaze and place on cake rack to drain.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Put the potatoes on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt to your own tastes.
Add all other ingredients.
Top with cheese. Cover and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: lemon-pepper breadsticks
directions: Mix lemon peel, water, lemon juice, salt and pepper in small mixing bowl.
Arrange breadsticks on ungreased baking sheet, twisting ends in opposite directions a few times.
Brush breadsticks with lemon-pepper mixture.
Bake according to package directions.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Blend ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°, until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and margarine in a 9-inch square pan, stirring often.
Bake at 350° until brown in color. When cool, sprinkle 2/3 crumbs in long baking dish.

title: peanut butter burst cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream together the butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry mixture until well mixed.
Add 12 ounces peanut butter morsels.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Add vegetables and mix well. Combine milk, vinegar, sugar and Miracle Whip.
Add these ingredients to macaroni mixture.
Mix thoroughly and chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Makes 10 portions.

title: crusty cheese bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water; stir until dissolved.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, butter, cheese, eggs and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Add yeast mixture and dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Turn dough onto well floured surface.
Knead about 8 minutes or until smooth and satiny. Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Knead gently on floured surface for 2 minutes.
Shape into a 20-inch roll.
Place in a well-greased 9-inch ring mold.
Pinch edges to seal.
Cover.
Let rise until almost doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Yields 1 ring.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix the butter, sugars, egg, pineapple (drained) and vanilla. Add all dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili in a skillet
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain. Add onion, chili beans, macaroni and water.
Add chili powder, barbecue sauce, ketchup and mustard to taste. Stir all ingredients well. Simmer for about 1/2 hour. Sauce will thicken.
Cover with cheese. Let cheese melt. Serve.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown onion, then ground beef in skillet and drain.
Cook noodles and drain well.
Layer noodles and meat.
Scatter on cottage cheese, slices of Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Repeat layer, finishing with sauce.
(May need to add a little water if it looks dry.)
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain off all fat.
Put in crock-pot.
Add tomato paste, tomato juice, whole tomato, soup beans (wash and drain beans good), chili powder, red pepper and salt.
Cook all day on low.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook green beans until barely tender.
Let cool.
Fill quart jars with beans and into each jar add 1 tablespoon coarse pickling salt.
Fill with cold water and seal tightly.
Store in cool place.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Combine noodles with any of the following: tomatoes, green pepper, onion, broccoli, mushrooms, black olives, olives or pimentos.

title: chocolate-butterscotch scotcheroos
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring just to	a boil over moderate heat.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press, using wax paper, into buttered 13
x
9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water
the	chocolate
and butterscotch morsels.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 15 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: deviled crabmeat balls
directions: Combine crabmeat, onion, sherry, parsley, egg yolk, salt, pepper and mustard; blend until well mixed.
Shape teaspoon of the mixture into balls.
Grease baking pan with oil.
Lightly roll crabmeat balls in the bread crumbs.
Arrange on baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven 10 minutes or until browned.
Makes 32 appetizers. Each ball contains 10 calories.

title: kahlua
directions: Add sugar to the coffee and boil 2 minutes.
Cool and add vodka and vanilla.

title: pineapple cloud pie
directions: Combine cereal, brown sugar, and corn syrup.
Mix well. Using back of spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly on the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan that has been lightly coated with cooking spray.
Chill in refrigerator.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add pineapple.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture and pour into crust.
Freeze about 3 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with a cherry.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Add onion to fried bacon and saute.
Stir in ground beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.
This is delicious served with cornbread.

title: chicken cheesy noodles
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
In saucepan cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add soup and cubed Velveeta cheese.
Cook over medium-low heat until all cheese has melted and mixture becomes hot.
Stir often.
Add some leftover chicken broth to slightly thin cheese sauce.
Cook noodles according to package.
Combine chicken, noodles and sauce.
Mix well.
Kids love it!

title: crunchy punch
directions: Bring to a boil 9 cups water.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
In another boiler, bring to a boil sugar and water. Add this to jello mixture and let cool.
When cool, add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze this.

title: swiss rye bread
directions: Take top off loaf and cut grids 1 1/2-inches (almost to bottom).
Place 1 cut of
Swiss
cheese
in each slot, using 1 pound.
Place pan in round pan.
Blend together the balance of ingredients and spread
on top of bread like icing of cake and bake at 350°
for
minutes.
Remove
and
cool	2 minutes. (Good for a party.)

title: peanut butter ice cream sauce
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Heat to boiling and cook over low heat to soft ball stage (200°).
Remove from heat.
Cool, without stirring, to room temperature.
Blend in 1/2 cup peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Can be kept in refrigerator.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy saucepan.
Add milk, sugar and butter. Cook over medium heat to soft stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add almond bar and marshmallows.
Beat until melted. Quickly stir in coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in buttered 10 x 6 x 1-inch dish.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Mix well and serve.
Good for sandwich or dip.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into small balls, brown and drain off fat.
Add catsup, sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and 1/4 cup water.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes and stir.
Add pineapple chunks, cover and simmer until heated through.
Serve in a chafing dish.

title: chili
directions: Sweat chopped onions, peppers and garlic. Combine beans (optional), diced tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cook over medium-high heat until it begins to boil, then reduce to lowest heat and simmer. Add sweated vegetables and chili seasoning. Brown kielbasa or Italian sausage, cut into 1-inch cubes, then add to chili. Deglaze saute pan and add to chili. Add marinated, browned beef tips with sauce (reference other recipe). Simmer over low heat for 1 hour. Add salt and pepper to taste. If necessary, thicken with cornstarch.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix all the dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture. Beat well and stir in the diced zucchini.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: avocado dessert(portuguese)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth and creamy.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 5 minutes over medium heat the olive oil, onion and garlic. Stir in tomatoes, chili pepper, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, molasses and lemon juice. Simmer over medium/low heat until reduced by 1/4 volume, about 45 minutes. Stir often. Puree in blender; add salt and pepper to taste. Will keep in refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Grease baking dish with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry punch
directions: Make up 1 package of Kool-Aid and freeze in cubes.
Make up 1 package as to drink.
Chill Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.

title: crabmeat english muffin(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Spread on each half of English muffins.
Freeze until ready to broil.
Place frozen English muffins on cookie sheet; broil for 3 minutes or until golden; cut each muffin half into 6 wedges.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, margarine, and peanut butter; mix well. Press flat onto a cookie sheet. (I put a paper towel over it to absorb some of the excess oils). Put in the refrigerator.

title: granny williams' virginia sweet pickles
directions: Day 1:
Use whole cucumbers at first.
Wash and place in a stone jar.
Cover with a hot brine made by using 1 pint of salt to 1 gallon of boiling water.
Weight down and let stand for 6 days.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well; add apples and vanilla.
Beat more.
Add pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven for one hour.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar; beat until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until it holds very stiff peaks.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Make a depression in center and build up sides slightly.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 300°.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix in a separate bowl the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and pinch of salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Roll dough into balls and then roll into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: tangerine martini
directions: Fill cocktail shaker with ice.
Fill almost to top with tangerine-grapefruit juice.
Add 2-3 shots of lemon or orange flavored vodka and shake. Serve in a chilled martini glass with a stemmed cherry.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with honey.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add orange juice and oil.
Pour liquid over mixture of blended dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Dough will be quite soft but add a little more flour, if needed.
Roll out on well floured surface.
Cut into biscuits and place on oiled baking sheet; let rise until double.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Top with Orange Icing.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not stir or mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts according to package directions; drain.
Combine vinegar, oil, garlic, sugar, salt and Tabasco.
Add sprouts and onions.
Toss; cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Arrange on appetizer tray, with toothpicks, to serve.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler over hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Add finely chopped pickle, if desired.
Mix thoroughly.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cut in
the ingredients with pastry blender and chill 2 hours. Divide in
parts and roll each as circle on floured board. Use filling;
cut
in
pieces
and roll in crescent shape.

title: baby food cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: four layered dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and pecans together like pie crust. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cream cream cheese with powdered sugar until fluffy, then fold in 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Mix instant pudding with milk as directed on package. Pour over cream cheese mixture, then spread a layer of Cool Whip over top before serving.
Cut in squares and top with roasted pecans, if desired.

title: meringue drops
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place egg whites in large mixing bowl. Beat until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until soft peaks are formed when beaters are pulled up.
Add sugar a tablespoon at a time.
Beat until smooth and satiny.
Add extract. Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets covered with brown paper.
Shape into mounds the shape of a small walnut on top.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sole fillet
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of butter; saute celery and onions.
Stir in stuffing mix, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cut each fillet to make 8 to 10 pieces.
Place in a greased pan.
Top each with stuffing mixture.
Melt remaining butter and add dill.
Pour sauce over each fillet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: "yummy" strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add sliced bananas and chopped pecans.
Pour half of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and hold in refrigerator or freezer until firm.
Jell remaining half only to thicken.

title: speedy spicy chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, mix and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes. Top with sour cream and cheese.

title: meat with rice
directions: Brown
pork
chops or parboil chicken.
In baking dish, combine
uncooked
rice
and orange juice.
Place meat on top. Bake in a
oven for approximately 1 hour until liquid is gone.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Put in saucepan and dissolve over heat.
Cool and pour over slaw.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours and then freeze.

title: yeast bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Then add dry yeast. Melt butter and add water and milk to melted butter.
The water and milk need to be lukewarm.
Mix together liquid and dry mixture.
Let set for approximately 1 1/2 hours in greased pan to rise.
After this rises, make dough into a loaf or in rolls. Knead well before you shape your loaf or rolls.
Put this in a greased pan and let rise again to desired size.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Line the bottom and sides of a spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Put berries in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Cool.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix oats, coconut and walnuts; set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats mixture.
Quickly drop mixture by rounded teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: toffee popcorn
directions: Mix together
butter, sugar and syrup.
Cook to 305° or hard crack.
Add
2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Pour over 4 to 5 quarts popped
popcorn.
Add nuts and stir to cool.
Spread on waxed paper and cool.

title: danny koczuk's red cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage.
Saute onion in oil and cool; then toss with salad.
Add carrots and drained raisins.
Add vinegar/sugar mixture and salt/pepper and toss salad well.
Add dressing when ready to serve.
If serving on individual plates, add the dollop of dressing to the center of the salad; do not mix.

title: vegetable dip(with water chestnuts)
directions: Mix altogether and refrigerate.
Makes 4 cups.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, cake mix, butter together.
This makes a stiff dough.
Pat in greased cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, and powdered sugar together with electric mixer.
Pour over dough and bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes or until light brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell (shallow). Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: When cream cheese is room temperature, add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
This may be served in chafing dish.

title: biscuit pizza
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
In a bowl mix sauce and biscuits. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and toppings.
Mix together.
Pour in a deep-dish pie glass dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
In the last few minutes of cooking sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup of cheese over the top and put back into the oven until cheese is melted.

title: chicken dinner pie
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2-inch or 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning. Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 425°.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add to kidney beans.
Mix well.
Add sausage, onions and tomatoes.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raisin honey chews
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, honey, egg and orange peel.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats.
Add raisins.
Drop a teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake above oven center at 350° (about 5 to 6 minutes) or until tops begin to lightly brown. Let stand on baking sheet about 2 minutes, then remove with a spatula to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 60 to 70 small cookies. Keeps well in layered wax paper in a cake tin.
(You have to experiment with baking time in your oven.
If cooked too long, cookies are too firm/hard.)

title: spinach
directions: Drain spinach; then chop onion.
Add oil to skillet and saute onion and bacon.
Add spinach to onion and bacon.
Add salt and vinegar; cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Melt and cool chocolate.
Cream well sugar and butter.
Add 1 egg; beat for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate and blend.
Add 1 more egg; beat 5 minutes more.
Add vanilla.
Place in crust.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: rancho baked beans and hamburger
directions: In a skillet, fry beef and onions in 2 tablespoons shortening; drain. Then add salt, ketchup, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar, pork and beans and kidney beans to the beef mixture.
Bake in baking dish uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix smoked and fresh ham with eggs, milk and cracker crumbs and form into loaf.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard. Pour over loaf in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Baste often, like every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy(for breakfast)
directions: Add 1/2 cup cold milk to the sugar, flour and cocoa.
Stir until well blended.
Heat the remaining milk to boiling.
Mix together and heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla. Serve over biscuits and butter.

title: rhubarb, pineapple pie
directions: Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 375°; continue baking for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop a medium cabbage and boil until tender in salted water. Add butter, onion and soup; lightly stir.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over mixture.
Cook only until cheese and bread crumbs dissolve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.

title: iceberg dills
directions: Scrub fresh cucumbers and pack in sterilized jars.
Bring liquid ingredients and salt to a boil; pour over pickles and seal. Makes 6 quarts pickles.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add salt and baking powder to graham crackers.
Add this mixture to margarine and sugar, alternating with milk.
Add pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Sift flour and spices.
Mix all together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers/bread.
Heat until smooth.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in microwave.
Cool a few seconds.
Mix in with Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Add salt and slowly sprinkle in cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, then lower heat to low and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat in, one at a time, 3 to 4 egg yolks.
Beat egg whites to stiff peak.
Fold into mush mix.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until top is golden and knife blade inserted comes clean.
Serve immediately with butter and warm syrup.

title: fresh horseradish
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and process at grind until finely grated.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix together in crockpot and cook on low 6 to 7 hours.

title: special mustard dip
directions: Mix all but mayonnaise in double boiler and cook until thick. Let cool.
Then add equal parts of mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: peppy mex snack
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In small roasting pan, combine cereal, pretzels and peanuts.
In small saucepan, melt margarine; stir in seasonings.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture; stir gently to coat.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once during baking.
Yield:
11 cups.

title: punch
directions: Heat 1 quart water to dissolve sugar.
Mix everything together and freeze.
Remove from freezer the night before so punch will be slushy.
Easy and really good.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Mix and place in preheated oven (400°); immediately reduce to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes and let stand a few more minutes before cutting.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream together margarine and peanut butter. Blend Rice Krispies in blender.
Add to mixture with confectioners sugar. Roll mixture into small buckeye size balls. Let cool in fridge.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown beef until done.
Drain well.
Add onions and jalapeno peppers.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, milk and 1 cup corn with cornbread mix.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour half of batter into greased 9-inch pan.
Top with beef mixture, cheese slices and remaining cup of corn.
Pour remaining half of batter on top of this and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rhubarb on top of mix.
Sprinkle sugar over the rhubarb layer.
Drizzle whipping cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Pour
over
apples,
spreading
