to the edge. Bake at 375° until brown and crisp. Serve warm.

title: snappy green beans
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Cook onion with basil in drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and stir often. Garnish with bacon.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except poppy seed, with hands as you would for biscuits.
Bake in small casserole dish at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top of bread before baking.
Brush with melted margarine while still hot.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well in a large bowl butter and honey. Stir in egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Pour flour mixture into butter mixture and stir well.
Add chocolate chips, raisins, chopped nuts or granola or any combination of these.
Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown (do not overbake).
Cool.
Store tightly covered.

title: corn muffins
directions: Spray 6 muffin cups with Pam.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients and divide equally into muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine the first ten ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Fold in nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with walnut halves.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake 40 to 45 minutes, shielding top with foil if necessary to prevent overbrowning.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 stick margarine (melted), cheese and diced eggs.
Other 1/2 stick of margarine in bottom of casserole, layer of crumbs, then asparagus.
Alternate having crumbs on top.
Cover with diluted soup.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.
Green beans can be used in lieu of asparagus.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onion in shortening until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 50 minutes. Heat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Arrange potato slices on meat.
Stir together soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and meat are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in pineapple juice over low heat, folding over and over until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Blend pineapple, carrots and cheese.
When the gelatin is cool, blend together all ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart ring mold. Serve garnished with lettuce and with salad dressing.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine and blend in flour.
Stir milk in slowly.
Cook until thick.
Stir in salt and grated cheese.
Pour over onions.
Bake at 375° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl mix sugars, shortening, margarine, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir in the first mixture; add chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls two inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mash the avocado with lemon juice.
Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer all ingredients in dish in order listed.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and creamy. Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese monkey bread
directions: Thaw bread completely; cut into pieces.
Cut cheese into small blocks and tear off pieces of bread dough and wrap around cheese.
Dip into melted butter and place around Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until good and brown.
Turn onto serving plate and pull apart.

title: nan's light fruitcake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine pecans, walnuts, cherries, pineapple and raisins.
Toss with 1 cup flour; make sure everything is covered with flour.
Set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in lemon extract.
Sift together 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Add in thirds to the creamed mixture.
Mix well to coat all fruits and nuts.
Transfer batter to well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover tightly with foil.

title: cindi's clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Add enough water to clam juice to make 1 cup.
Stir clams, liquid, potatoes, celery and spices in bacon and onion mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk; heat, but do not boil.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix sugar mixture with apples and place in pie shell.
Mix together 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Cut butter into flour mixture until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbs over pie.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°, until crumbs are slightly brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Reserve 3 to 4 tablespoons for topping.
Press remainder in bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: angel fruit dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
In 3 quart bowl spread some cake.
Pour on some pudding and then some pie filling.
Repeat in layers.
May top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: cheese balls
directions: Roll in nuts and bacon bits.

title: hot pepper rice
directions: Wash, trim and dry potatoes.
Grease skins, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking until potatoes are soft.
It takes about an hour for medium potatoes or 1 1/2 hours for large ones.
Turn off heat and leave potatoes in oven to cook, if desired.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fired onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple butter muffins
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, 1/3 cup sugar, baking powder, apple pie spice or pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mix.
Stir just until moistened.
Line muffin pans with paper.
Spoon a round tablespoon of batter into each.
Top each with a rounded teaspoon of apple butter and then with the remaining batter.
Combine pecans and 2 tablespoons sugar; sprinkle atop batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Beat butter in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Cream well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, lemon extract, juice and rind.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.

title: verna's fudge stripe salad
directions: Mix
together
the
buttermilk and pudding with a spoon until the the mixture is smooth. Fold in the thawed Cool Whip. Drain the mandarin oranges and pineapple tidbits well and add the fruit
to the
mixture (other fruits may be substituted). Use the bottom of a glass to crush the cookies (not too fine) and add the cookies to the salad. Refrigerate.

title: tortilla roll-ups #2
directions: Mix all of the above
together and spread on tortillas. Roll up and
secure
with toothpick.
Chill for several hours, then cut in bite
sized
bits and serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix in a glass bowl and let set 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: date balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, dates and nuts.
Cook for about 10 minutes on low heat and add Rice Krispies.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: turkey wild rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the chicken broth and water.
Add rice and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Lightly spoon the flour into a measuring cup; level off.
In a medium saucepan, melt the margarine; stir in flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in half and half (milk); cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Slowly add milk mixture into rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat gently; do not boil.
Stir frequently.
Garnish with additional green onions and bacon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Toss together bread cubes, apples, cheese and raisins.
Combine butter, orange juice, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over bread mixture and toss gently.
Stuff pork chops.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pie shells and set aside.
Mix apple juice, cornstarch and cinnamon until smooth and well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until it boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add apples and stir until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes.
Can use 2 crusts or prepare as a Dutch apple with cinnamon, brown sugar and margarine mixed together and sprinkled over top.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot until tender, 60 to 90 minutes. Remove meat from bones.
Put the bones and skin back in the pot and boil for another 90 minutes for chicken broth for noodles or other dishes.
Cut the meat into bite size pieces and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Mix in both cans of soup and the peas.
Prepare the stuffing as to the directions on the box. Spread over the chicken and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (uncovered).
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: brady's coleslaw
directions: In a small bowl combine cabbage, carrot and green pepper.
In a small bowl combine vinegar, mayonnaise, minced onion, lemon juice, sugar, celery seed, salt (if desired) and pepper, mixing them well. Pour dressing over cabbage mixture.
Toss the slaw and chill it for at least 2 hours, tossing it again just before serving.
Dressing is excellent with other salads.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen rolls.

title: oven stew
directions: Put in well covered casserole in a 325° oven for 3 1/2 hours. If you wish, potatoes may be added the last hour or so.
Cover again.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cut the lard into the mixture.
Add the beaten eggs.
Add the sugar and milk.
Roll and cut.
Makes 68 small crinkle edge cookies or 4 dozen large ones. Sprinkle sugar on top.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: In large bowl, add potatoes, cut-up green pepper, onion, pimentos, parsley flakes, cubed Velveeta cheese and bread.
Add melted butter.
Place all in crock-pot.
Add milk to moisten.

title: cucumber, celery and radish salad(armenia)
directions: Peel and dice cucumbers; add radishes, celery and nuts.
Beat oil, lemon juice, salt and vinegar with electric mixer or blender; combine with vegetables.
Toss. Garnish with olives.
Walnuts may be substituted for pistachio nuts.
Yields 6 servings.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange chicken.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; brush on chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: lemon filling for cakes
directions: Combine sugar, starch and salt in saucepan.
Add water, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon peel and butter.
Stir until well blended.
Chill.
Use for filling in cakes.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Preheat oil in frying pan.
Add lemon pepper to buttermilk and mix well.
Dip mushrooms in mixture; roll in flour.
Deep-fry in oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with dressing of your choice.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise and curry powder together.
In baking dish, add broccoli and chicken, then pour mixed ingredients on top, then add cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven until bubbles in middle.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Cover cabbage with cold water.
Sprinkle salt on it.
Let set for 2 hours; drain.
Bring to boil 1/2 cup water, sugar, vinegar and mustard seed; cool thoroughly.
Put cabbage in glass jar. Pour in solution and cover lightly.
Do not seal.
Ready to use in 1 hour.
Keep in refrigerator.
Good for 6 months.

title: john gozzo's beef stew
directions: Cut beef into bite-sized cubes.
In Dutch oven or heavy saucepan, heat the olive oil and add onions and bay leaves.
Cook slowly for approximately 10 minutes.
Add meat, rosemary and black pepper and brown for an additional 10 minutes.
Lightly sprinkle the flour over the meat.
Add chopped garlic and parsley to meat. (Optional:
Add 1/2 cup dry white wine at this time.)
Simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Add celery, green pepper and carrots. Stir.
Cover and cook slowly for approximately 20 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Layer in order of listing. Bake in preheated 350° oven until bubbly and hot.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips. I bake mine on a cookie sheet.

title: steak and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Season cube steak with salt and pepper; peel and slice the potatoes thin.
Place potatoes in the bottom of the baking dish and the cube steak on top of the potatoes.
Mix the 2 cans of soup with 1 can of water and pour over the steak and potatoes.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese melts. Remove and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt enough margarine in pan to keep it all from sticking to the bottom. I sprinkle parsley flakes and black pepper in there too. Sometimes I add white shoepeg corn or a little Mrs. Dash seasoning. You can switch and change as you please with this one.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the ketchup; put in loaf pan and pour ketchup over the top of the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Peel potatoes and onion.
Place ground beef, potatoes, onion and parsley in large soup pot.
Cover with water.
Puree tomatoes in blender.
Add to pot.
Salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan. Add hash browns. Sprinkle onions and cheese. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over hash browns. Sprinkle corn flakes or French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Place ice cubes in large pitcher.
Add a few strawberries. Pour in cranberry juice cocktail.
Carefully pour lemon-lime drink down the inside of pitcher.
Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato fruit salad
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut off any woody portions and ends.
Cook in boiling water for 25 minutes, or just until tender; cool.
Peel and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Finely shred 1 teaspoon orange peel and set aside.
Peel and section oranges.
Place oranges in a large bowl.
Add potatoes, grapes, raisins, celery and nuts.
In a small bowl combine orange peel, cream cheese and honey until smooth; stir in 2 tablespoons orange juice.
Pour over mixture and toss to coat. Cover and chill.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll into ball, then roll in pecans.

title: hershey's toffee crunch blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Stir flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat butter and brown sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups of toffee bits and chocolate chips.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges begin to pull away from the sides of pan.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup toffee bits.
Cool completely. Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: cream tacos
directions: Saute
onions in butter; add soup and cream.
Add Cheez Whiz. Make
into
sauce.
Layer
tortillas.
Add
shredded chicken, then sauce.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken to even thickness using palm of hand or flat side of meat mallet.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly roll fashion. Tuck in ham and cheese.
If necessary, secure with wooden toothpicks.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken rolls 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; pour into an 11 x 13-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, mix the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cake and swirl with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add buttermilk and hot water; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Toss vegetables with dressing and let marinate in refrigerator at least overnight.

title: hungarian marsetti(from 1975 edition)
directions: Add 1 teaspoon of salt to 2 or 3 quarts of water.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Drain and pour hot water over noodles while still in colander.
Brown onion in a pan.
Add hamburg and brown while stirring.
Add noodles, cheese and tomatoes to hamburg.
Mix. Bake in casserole slowly in 300° to 325° oven for about 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Microwave fruit on High until hot.
Mix biscuit mix, sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine and stir lightly to blend.
Pour hot fruit evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish with pastry; trim excess pastry around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick with a fork.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Cook hen.
Debone and cut in bite-sizes.
In half of broth, cook until tender, bell pepper and celery.
In other half of broth, cook noodles and add American cheese, mushroom soup, sliced mushrooms, pimiento and sliced chestnuts.
Put all in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: easy m&m cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, oleo, eggs and 1/4 cup water, mixing well (dough will be stiff).
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by tablespoons on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet, remove and cool on wire rack.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cherry pineapple cake
directions: Place pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread over all to make the bottom layer.
Add the pineapple in a layer over the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle the entire box of cake mix evenly over all.
Dot the margarine over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1 1/2 packages of the dried beef, green onion, sauce and seasoned salt.
Roll into ball and roll in remaining chopped beef (real fine) until well covered and chill.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use fresh orange juice if too dry.

title: potluck tuna
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and saute celery and onion until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickens.
Add cheese, tuna and vegetables.
Pour into casserole. Top with biscuits.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except cheese. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lo-cal milkshake
directions: Mix in blender until ice is gone.

title: dip for tostitos chips
directions: Cook sausage and drain on towels.
Melt cheese and add all ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Grill to keep warm.
Serve with chips.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add 1 egg at a time.
Add sugar to this.
Add vanilla and blend.
Dredge with 1/2 cup flour the dates, orange slices, nuts and coconut.
Add to batter.
Butter and flour pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: foolproof pie crust(makes 5 pie shells)
directions: Mix well together water, vinegar and egg.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add mixture of water, vinegar and egg; mix with fork. Make into 5 equal parts, like a hamburger patty.
Wrap each separately and chill several hours or overnight.
Freeze if any left over.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Can be baked in 9 x 13-inch pan or in two 8-inch or 9-inch layer pans.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and coffee crystals together and set aside.
In mixing bowl, put shortening; gradually add sugar to shortening, creaming well.
Add eggs to creamed mixture one at a time.
Add vanilla and red food coloring.
Add buttermilk with dry ingredients, beat smooth after each addition.
Into boiling water, add soda.
Pour over batter and mix until smooth (batter will be thin).
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crispy corncakes
directions: In a medium bowl, pour boiling water over cornmeal; cool.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Mix egg, milk and butter with cornmeal mixture; stir into flour mixture until blended.
Mixture will be runny.
On a heated griddle or skillet sprayed with non-stick cooking spray, drop mixture by tablespoonfuls.
Cook over medium heat until bottom is crispy brown and top looks dry; turn and brown other side.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: low-fat cream cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Blend the following items with a hand mixer: 1 box cake mix, 1 egg substitute (1/4 cup), 1 cup liquid margarine substitute and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch glass casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.

title: tympani taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and combine with the marshmallows.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Mix in saucepan over medium heat and cool until thick the pineapple juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, take sauce and mix with Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill 8 hours.

title: super delicious cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Shape as desired into loaf, balls or patties.
Fry or broil as usual.
For meat loaf, place on greased foil in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: chicken no-fat fry with onions
directions: Cut chicken in serving size pieces.
Place chicken, skin side down, in a single layer in a large frying pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; place onion slices on top.
Cover tightly.
(No need to add any fat.)
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Tilt lid slightly so liquid will evaporate; continue cooking 20 minutes longer or until chicken is tender and golden.
Place chicken on a heated serving platter, pushing onions back into pan; stir in water, mixing with browned bits from bottom of pan.
Cook until liquid evaporates.
Spoon over chicken.

title: summer spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a shallow roasting pan.
In a bowl mix remaining ingredients; pour sauce over ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Prepare topping and set aside.

title: easy cherry cream cheese dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine pudding mix and milk; beat well to mix ingredients. Add cream cheese; continue to beat until smooth and thickened.
Pour into custard cups or large serving dish. Top with pie filling and refrigerate until serving time.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, meal, soda, buttermilk and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in a hot greased pan and bake like regular corn bread until done.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: easy homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Debone chicken; place in baking dish, 13 x 9-inches.
Slice butter all over chicken.
Spread 1 can English peas (drained) over chicken and butter.
Cook celery and carrots together.
Put these on top of peas.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Pour over preceding mixture.
Mix together chicken broth and soup.
Pour this mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon rarebit
directions: Drain and flake the salmon.
Cook frozen peas as directed on package.
Mix salmon and peas together, adding salt and pepper as desired.
Spread mixture into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Grate cheese and sprinkle over mixture.
Pour 1/2 c. milk over top.
Combine Bisquick, mayonnaise and 1/3 c. milk.
Drop by spoonfuls over top.
Bake uncovered at 450° for 10-15 minutes.

title: ruby red salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Combine sugar and syrup and bring to a boil. Then add peanut butter and vanilla. Grease a bowl and put corn flakes in it. Pour cooked mixture over corn flakes and mix well. Drop from spoon on waxed paper. Makes about 24.

title: pound cake squares
directions: Melt butter; add
pound
cake
and 2 eggs.
Mix and pat into a 9 x
13-inch
pan.	Then
mix
cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (minus
the 1/2 cup).
Pour this mixture on top of the other.
Sprinkle
nuts
on	top.
Bake
at	350° for 35 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package.
Drain.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add chili and corn; simmer on low 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and top with cheese.
Cover and heat on low 5 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Stir-fry all the ingredients in a little oil, add taco seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
After done, heat your flour soft shell, put in your fajita meat, then add diced tomato, shredded cheese and picante sauce.
Roll up and eat.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender; drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup and sour cream.
Spread in casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake 20 minutes.
Bake 3/4 hour in slow oven at 350°.

title: pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook linguine in boiling water according to package, drain. Keep warm.
Coat skillet or wok with canola oil and heat to medium (325°).
Add frozen Chinese stir-fry and garlic to hot oil and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat and add olives, tomatoes, basil and parsley.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove wok from heat and add cooked linguine and Parmesan cheese.
Gently toss mixture.
Serve hot.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix with margarine and 1 egg until coarse and crumbly.
Pat in bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend in blender for 3 minutes on low.
Pour into pie plate and let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top and press down.
Cook on 350° for 40 minutes.

title: a favorite icing
directions: This is a cake icing I like to make for loaf cakes or cinnamon rolls.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to first mixture.
Place in two 5 x 9-inch pans or one large pan.
(Should not be too thick.)
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: littleneck clams and shrimp with tomato sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and seasoning in large pot (should be "very spicy" from hot pepper).
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add littlenecks; cover and cook on high until clams open up.
Lower heat; add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are done.
Serve with fresh bread.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Mix all together but the oleo and vanilla.
Cook about 5 minutes, then add oleo and vanilla.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until blended.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13 glass pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: company for breakfast
directions: Cover 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Grate both cheeses on top. Layer with browned bacon slices.
Beat milk and eggs and pour into pan.
Cover overnight in refrigerator.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Cook sausage meat until brown (then drain grease).
Mix cheese, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Let cool 15 minutes and spread on bread.
Put under broiler until bubbly, then serve.

title: hamburger skillet meal
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown onion in butter until tender. Add cornstarch, salt, bouillon, Kitchen Bouquet and water, stirring constantly, until thick. Simmer 10 minutes. Combine hamburger, seasoned salt and pepper. Form into oval patties and fry until done. Add to sauce and let simmer 5 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Top will be golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Add 3/4 cup of wine or water to taco mix in a frying pan. Saute diced chicken strips in pan with taco seasoning for about 20 to 25 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: a delicious way to broil fish
directions: This method is excellent with a firm fish like salmon, halibut or swordfish cut as filet or steak.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; brown in oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes, basting chicken with sauce occasionally.
Add apricots and green pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in 2 1/2-quart covered casserole in microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: fluffy lime dessert
directions: In small
saucepan melt butter or oleo.
Stir in crumbs. Pat firmly in bottom of 11 x 17-inch pan.
Chill.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix in order given and bake in large casserole for about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
If you see it getting too dry, reduce heat.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve 1/2 of marshmallows in hot jello.
When cool, add rest of ingredients and remaining marshmallows.
Chill and serve.

title: pheasant hash
directions: Melt margarine in a large covered frypan (or electric pan). Add potatoes and brown.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Serves 4 to 6.

title: grasshopper salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: shrimp manale
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine black pepper, salt, white pepper, butter, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Mix well.
Add shrimp and stir into mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until shrimp are done.
Great with yellow rice.

title: superb slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight. Serve cold.
May be kept in the refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend pumpkin with sugar.
Beat eggs with milk.
Mix pumpkin with egg and milk mixture, vanilla, flour and spices.
Add melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: basting sauce for gas grill
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
In a measuring cup,
mix ingredients and fill to 1 cup with vinegar.
Add to melted oleo and cook until thick (about 3 minutes).
Brush over both sides of meat while cooking.

title: chocolate kraut cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Then sift again. Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy, add vanilla, eggs, one at at time, beating after each addition. Add dry ingredients alternately with water. Add kraut and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 375° about 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: chinese noodle cookies(microwave)
directions: Melt chips in microwave on High 1 or 2 minutes, until melted. Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls on aluminum foil.
Chill.

title: rice pie
directions: Boil rice with salt until cooked, then strain.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and grated orange and lemon skins and cool.
Break eggs in bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, allspice and Anisette; beat together.
Strain Ricotta cheese, then add milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Add orange and lemon juice and Anisette.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Grease well around cake pan.

title: iowa brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy. Beat in chocolate syrup and eggs one at a time. Beat in flour gradually and fold in nuts. Pour into greased jellyroll pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Do not overbake. Cool completely in pan before frosting.

title: shanghai chicken stew
directions: In a deep skillet or Dutch oven, heat oil and saute first 3 ingredients until soft.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomatoes and cook another 2 minutes.
Wrap peppercorns, cloves and cinnamon in a small piece of cheesecloth. Add chicken, cheesecloth package, water and Worcestershire sauce to onion mixture.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add veggies and continue to simmer, covered, until thoroughly cooked (about 20 minutes).
Remove cheesecloth package and serve stew steaming hot. Serves 8 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine water, sugar or honey, dry milk, salt and oil in pan. Heat to 120° to 130°.
Stir together whole wheat flour and yeast in bowl.
Add warm liquid and beaten eggs.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer 1/2 minute.
Scrape sides and bottom.
Then beat high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in rest of flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours, punch down.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Make into loaves or rolls.
Bake at 350°.

title: baseball mitt
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package.
Spoon into crust.
Spoon whipped topping over pudding and edge of crust to cover, mounding it to resemble a ball and smoothing the surface. Break cookies in half.
Tuck 3 broken halves into pudding, slightly overlapping around upper edge of crust.
Put another half cookie slightly to the left of other fingers for thumb.
Draw 2 half circles and stitching on ball with gel.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with mixture of melted margarine and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Spread in greased 16 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Pat it out and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven when it begins to turn delicately brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and red coloring and add to mixture.
Add milk alternately with flour and salt.
Mix baking soda and vinegar together and add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut layers in half to make 4 layers.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Make ice cream balls about the size of a tennis ball. Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a bowl. Pour milk in another bowl. Dip the ice cream balls in the milk, then dip the balls into the sugar mixture. Take the balls and dip into milk again. Crush the corn flakes and dip the balls into the crushed corn flakes. Roll balls until covered, refrigerate for 3 hrs. Then fry at 350 degrees for 6 minutes.

title: chili and beans
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes, salt, spices and water.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add chili beans the last 20 minutes of cooking time.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: two way brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and lightly flour bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter and eggs by hand; stir well.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate pieces.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2/3 of the batter and spread into prepared pan.
To remaining batter, add coconut, water and extract.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Yields 3 dozen bars.

title: indonesian cheese ball
directions: Mix.
Place peanuts or pecans all over surface of cheese ball.

title: sanbakkels
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add eggs and extract and mix well.
Add flour just enough to handle.
Press into molds, making as thin as possible.
Bake until light brown. Cool in tins, then remove.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Alternate blending into mixture dry ingredients and milk. Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hominy
directions: Dissolve lye in the 6 quarts of water, then add the corn and let stand for 15 hours.
Drain lye water from corn.
Add more cold water and wash thoroughly several times to remove corn hulls and lye.
Rubbing in a soft bag helps to remove hulls.
All hulls and black tips should be off.
If corn is discolored soak overnight in clear water and small amount of salt.
Drain.
Add fresh water and 5 tablespoons salt.
Boil 3 to 4 hours in a large covered kettle. Change water once or twice while cooking.
Be sure to keep kettle covered.
Makes 15 to 20 quarts of hominy.
Very good.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Don't use beef broth until tallow is removed.
Grind all meat, potatoes, onions and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients; add broth back to it.
Cook in large pot until thick as desired.
Put in containers.

title: baked beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine beans, onion, catsup, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Add a small amount of hot water to cocoa, enough to make liquid paste (thick but slightly runny).
Heat milk to lukewarm, then remove from heat.
Add part of milk to flour/sugar mixture to make runny paste.
Add flour/sugar/milk mixture to milk in pot. Turn on fire, stirring constantly.
Add beaten eggs, stir and cook. Add cocoa mixture until desired taste and color.
Cook to thicken. Do not boil, stirring often.
Pour through strainer into ice cream freezer.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer instructions.

title: dinner rolls italiano
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups all-purpose flour, active dry yeast and Italian seasoning.
Heat milk, water, sugar, butter and garlic salt until warm, 115° to 120°.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs. Beat at low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Using an additional 3 to 3 1/2 cups all-purpose flour, add as much as you can stir.
Turn out on floured surface and knead in enough flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Shape into ball.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double, 45 minutes.

title: one minute chocolate wafer pie crust
directions: Microwave butter in a 9-inch glass pie plate at High for 1 minute.
Stir in the wafer and walnut crumbs.
Press mixture evenly in the pie plate.
Chill, pour pie filling into shell and freeze.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and melted margarine.
Add nuts and make out like fingers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot, until well coated.

title: cheese roll
directions: Roll the Velveeta between waxed paper until about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with the cream cheese.
Spread layer of chopped green onions with tops.
Spread layer of chopped green chilies (large can) and chopped (pickled) jalapenos.
Roll up like a jelly roll and sprinkle top with paprika.
Place with seam down on a platter and cover with plastic wrap.
Chill until set.
When ready to serve, slice crosswise and serve with Fritos or Wheat Thins to dip with.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with vegetable spray. Line pan with 1 can crescent rolls. Mix rest of ingredients and spoon over crescent rolls. Place other can of crescent rolls on top of mixture. Beat egg whites with fork and spread on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool. Glaze with powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon milk.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Cook cucumbers, onions, cauliflower, green tomatoes and red peppers in salted water until tender, not mushy.
Drain and cover until the following mixture is ready.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except grapes, noodles, soup and milk.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken mixture.
Place noodles and grapes gently around edge.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the corn, rice and eggs.
Saute the first 7 ingredients until tender.
Mix well.
Bake in large casserole for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix in a 6-quart saucepan.
Cook until soft ball stage on a candy thermometer. Cool until just warm.
Beat well.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan.
Cut when firm.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat egg; add cake mix and Cool Whip.
Mix well and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until potatoes are soft, then add milk.
(Don't dump water out of potatoes.)
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick and easy country style steak
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour.
Roll steaks in seasoned flour.
Brown steaks in margarine.
remove to baking pan.
Mix soup and water and heat to boiling with steak drippings.
Pour soup over steaks.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken velveeta
directions: Boil chicken until good and tender.
Pull meat off of bone. Cup up or dice bell pepper and onion.
Put chicken pieces and diced bell pepper and onion, plus can of diced Ro-Tel together. Then cut cheese up in cubes; put everything together.
Stir plus 1 quart of chicken broth.
Boil some long noodles; when they get tender, put noodles only with other ingredients with a lid on it, then put it in the oven and cook until everything is tender.

title: melting dreams
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Measure out 1 tablespoon for each cookie.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and push down the top of cookie with fork in both directions.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese per directions on box.
Using a 2-quart casserole dish, pour in macaroni and cheese, cream of mushroom soup and the can of tuna.
Add about 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir all together.
Shred 1 more cup of cheese and spread on top.
Crumble some crackers and cover top.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sunday brunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender and drain.
Stir in melted margarine and beaten egg.
Add cheese, leaving enough to sprinkle on top.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix mustard and salt with 1 teaspoon hot water; add milk, then pour mixture over casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until custard is set and top is a crusty golden brown.

title: oyster cracker snack mix
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Coat crackers well with mixture. Spread mixture onto cookie sheet and let dry for 1 hour.
Store in airtight container.

title: mildred's swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and salt gradually, creaming well. Add almonds.
Mix. Blend in flour and mix thoroughly.
Blend in water and vanilla.
Shape in small round balls and flatten slightly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dip in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix
sugar
and
cornstarch;
add
vinegar, beet juice, butter and
salt.
Boil
five minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add beets and let cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: apple pie(dessert)
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt.
Mix with apples.
Prepare pastry; fill.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust; brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake in 375° oven 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice pickles, onions and green pepper very thin and mix.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and salt together.
Let set for 1 hour and stir often before adding to pickles, onions and green pepper.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 3 months.

title: necie's apple pie
directions: Place bottom layer of pie crust in pie pan.
Peel apples, dice and place in pie crust.
Top apples with sugars, water, nutmeg, cinnamon, lemon juice and vanilla.
Cut butter in small pieces over mixture.
Top with remaining pie crust.
Use fork to make tiny holes on top.
Sprinkle with a little sugar, nutmeg and butter slices.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cauliflower medley
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add cauliflowerets and cook covered over low heat 10 to 12 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add peas, salt and dash of pepper; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in pimiento. Serves 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Put all the ingredients together and simmer until mixed.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine until like coarse corn meal.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, with a fork, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: In saucepan, place all ingredients, except oatmeal, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Chill until firm.

title: christmas fruit cookies(my favorites)
directions: Cream together brown sugar, butter, eggs and soda mixture. Sift together three times flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Chop and mix with dry ingredients cherries, pineapple, raisins and pecans.
Mix in the butter and sugar, then add 1/2 cup orange juice (frozen) and mix with hands.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
It is a good substitute for fruit cake and much easier to make.
Store in airtight container for a week.

title: quick, sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together by hand. Form into balls. Place apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oven baked scrambled eggs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle cheese in square 9 x 9-inch pan. Dot with butter.
Mix cream, mustard, salt and pepper; pour half over cheese.
Pour eggs over top, then remaining cream mixture. Bake 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter candy cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, milk and vanilla.
With a wooden spoon blending dry ingredients.
Pour into large greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 20 minutes.
Right from oven, spread on peanut butter, allow to cool, melt chocolate bars and spread on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one baking sheet at a time for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: enchilada stack
directions: Cook ground beef over medium-high heat until browned.
Pour off fat.
Add 1/2 cup enchilada sauce.
Spray baking sheet with cooking spray.
Place 1 tortilla on sheet, then top with 1/3 of meat mixture and 1/4 cup of cheese.
Top with 1 tortilla, 1/2 of refried beans, 1/2 enchilada sauce, 1 can chilies and 1/4 cup cheese.
Repeat all layers.
Top with 1 tortilla, remaining meat mixture and 1/4 cup cheese.
Top with remaining tortilla.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until hot.
Uncover; top with remaining enchilada sauce and cheese.
Bake 5 minutes. Cut into wedges.
Serves 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet until lightly browned; pour off excess fat.
Add catsup, water, mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on buns. Serves 4.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring 5 cups water, sugar and cloves to a boil. Boil 5 minutes. Set aside.
Bring 8 cups water and tea bag(s) to a boil. Set aside and let steep 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients together and heat just below boiling point.
Let cool and store in refrigerator.
Heat as needed.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Wash, quarter and core the apples.
Place them in a large cooking pot and add the water.
Over medium heat, cook the apples until they are nearly soft.
Add the sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook the mixture for a few minutes longer, then press it through a strainer and let it cool.
Serve it warm or cold. Makes about 5 cups applesauce.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Melt margarine, cool and mix with pecans and flour.
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package; drain.
Arrange 4 noodles to cover bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook onion in butter until just tender; blend in cream cheese. Stir in cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Spread half atop noodles.
Combine soup, milk and wine.
Stir in shrimp and crab.
Spread half over cottage cheese layer.
Repeat layers of noodles, cheese mixture and seafood mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with shredded American cheese.
Bake until cheese melts, 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Melt in double boiler peanut butter morsels.
Stir until smooth; set aside.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
Combine butter and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in melted morsels.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Alternately blend in flour and milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In medium bowl stir strawberries, eggs and oil.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix into strawberry mixture.
Stir only to blend.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Chop onion; add vinegar, catsup, brown sugar and mustard.
Mix well.
Add ground beef and add water, if needed.
Add meat to catsup mixture and heat to boiling.

title: summertime-anytime-slush
directions: Mix
all ingredients together in a freezer-proof bowl with lid and freeze.
Stir it a couple of times while it's freezing.
Mix well, not freeze solid, it remains slushy because of alcohol.

title: south-of-the-border chips
directions: Cut corn tortillas into triangles.
Fry until brown or crispy. Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place bowl on plate with chips arranged around it.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix everything, but eggs and oil, and pour into a buttered pan.
Beat eggs and oil and pour over mixture.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: german pot casserole
directions: Place the beef, celery, potato slices and carrot slices in greased casserole in the order listed.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix on potatoes and carrots.
Put the soup on top.
Cover; bake for 1 1/8 hours in a 350° oven.
Top with onions the last 10 minutes.

title: tangy tomato aspic
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in tomato sauce, vinegar and seasonings.
Chill until slightly thickened, but not set.
Stir in celery.
Pour into 4-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease 1/2-quart casserole with butter.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple impromptu
directions: Place apples in well-greased 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with mixer until fluffy.
Add pineapple, well drained of juice.
Pour into large glass dish and cover with clear wrap.
Let sit overnight.

title: cutlets supreme
directions: Beat eggs in milk.
Roll meat in egg mixture, then cracker crumbs.
Roll meat second time in eggs and crackers.
Fry in medium hot oil slowly until done.
Cover meat with cheese.
Cover pan until cheese melts.

title: meatballs cantonese
directions: Combine beef, celery, almonds, seasoned salt, bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and eggs.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in cornstarch and brown in hot oil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes; turn often.
Drain fat.
Blend remaining soy sauce, drained pineapple plus water to make 2 cups, and 3 tablespoons cornstarch; pour over meatballs and heat.
Add green pepper after meatballs and sauce are heated.
Serve over rice, if wished.

title: crunchy potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour potatoes in bottom.
Mix soup, mushrooms, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper. Pour over potatoes.
Mix butter and corn flake crumbs and sprinkle on top after casserole has baked 45 minutes covered with foil. Bake until brown after adding crumbs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in loaf pan.
Crunch cornflakes over top.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: four cheese baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Butter a 2 quart ovenproof casserole dish and set aside.
Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water until al dente.
Drain.
Bring half and half, basil, and crushed red pepper to a simmer in a large saucepan over medium high heat.
Add cheeses one handful at a time, stirring constantly until cheeses are melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in pasta and spoon into prepared dish.
Bake until heated through, approximately 10 minutes.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles and drain.
Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms to hamburg.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil green tomatoes and chiles in a large pot until ready. Blend them in a blender until saucy.
In a heated pan, put oil. Add the tortillas and cook until soft.
Pour sauce in another pan and place tortillas over it.
Put the tortillas on a plate and put chicken in it.
Fold it like a taco.
Put cheese, lettuce and tomatoes over it.
Enjoy.

title: champagne punch
directions: Blend fruit juices and vodka, then add ginger ale.
Pour over sherbet and ice cubes.
In a punch bowl, blend, then add strawberries and pour champagne on top.

title: manicotti cheese bake
directions: Saute meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add paste, water, salt, pepper, sugar and seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Parboil shells in salted water, approximately 6 minutes. Drain on paper towel.
Fill shells with combined Ricotta (or cottage), Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses and parsley.
Place shells in shallow baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spanish steaks
directions: Melt oil in skillet.
Saute onion and pepper until tender. Cut meat into serving pieces; season with salt and pepper and coat with flour.
Remove onions and peppers from pan.
Brown meat.
Top meat with onions and peppers.
Mix tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Pour over steak.
Cover tightly.
Cook slowly for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar in bowl. In separate bowl, mix milk and pudding. Fold in Cool Whip; mix with cream cheese mixture. Layer in deep bowl 1/3 crushed Oreo cookies, 1/2 pudding mixture, 1/3 cookies, rest of pudding and rest of cookies. Put in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Beat flour, sugar, cocoa and water; mix well.
Add oil and beat well.
Add salt, vanilla and baking soda, dissolved in vinegar; mix well.
Pour half of batter into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix and let cool in refrigerator, shape and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 300°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix with wooden spoon.	Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Use any brand or flavor of cake mix.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and cocoa.
In large bowl mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and cocoa mix.
Gradually add flour until well blended.
Add nuts and bake in greased 8 x 12-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mix in the pan carrot cake
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch square pan, mix dry ingredients.
Add carrots, eggs, oil, water and vanilla.
Mix well with a fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 9.

title: sweet potato carrot gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put sweet potatoes and carrots in pot; cover with water.
Bring to boil and cook for ten minutes or until tender.
In large bowl, combine next four ingredients (juice to salt and pepper).
Drain sweet potato mixture; add to bowl and toss to coat.
Transfer to casserole dish coated with nonstick spray and bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for ten minutes more.

title: homemade bread
directions: Soak yeast in warm water and sugar.
Let it stand for 5 minutes, then add flour
and salt.
Maybe you need more water. Knead.
Place in greased
pan
and
let
stand
in warm place, covered, until doubled.
Punch down and make into loaves.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: yum yum cobbler
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8 pan; mix the dry ingredients together and add milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour melted margarine over dough.
Place berries or fruit over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add milk gradually.
Mix in all other ingredients until smooth with wire
whisk.
Use vegetable oil or shortening to fry in skillet.
After brown, take out. Drain excess oil.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: brownies
directions: May use 2 1/2 cups self-rising flour and omit baking powder.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Saute the celery
and
onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Make
a
white sauce with the remaining butter, flour and milk.
Break up tomatoes with a wooden spoon and add to white sauce
and vegetables.
Add chopped parsley and heat. Do not allow to boil.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Clean vegetables and cut into chunks.
Place in blender and blend until medium fine.
Drain.
Combine mayonnaise, salt and cream cheese.
Add vegetable mixture and mix well.
Store covered overnight in refrigerator.
Spread on bread of your choice. Mixture can be made ahead of time and stored in airtight containers.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Slice chicken into very thin slices.
Mix chicken, cornstarch, sherry, ginger and 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt.
Set aside.

title: creamy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks; mash in small bowl.
Stir in dressing, relish, mustard and seasonings until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into centers of egg whites.
Cover. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 16.
(Preparation time: 25 minutes plus refrigerating.)

title: pie cake
directions: Empty pie filling into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Pat cake mix (dry) over pie filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour potato salad
directions: Cook eggs, margarine, vinegar and sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (about 12 minutes). If mixture becomes too thick, add a little milk.
If too lumpy, you may strain mixture.
Pour mixture over potatoes, onion and peppers and mix thoroughly.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix mashed strawberries and sugar.
Start with a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of strawberry mixture.
Alternate layers leaving the top layer strawberry mixture.
Top with cool whip and chill completely before serving.

title: "lucious layers" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 (9-inch) round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Add vegetables; allow to set in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep 10 days in refrigerator. Yields 12 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place 1/2 cup corn syrup and 1 cup sugar in large, heavy Pyrex mixing bowl.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add 1 cup peanuts. Microwave on High 3 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove.
Add and stir in baking soda.

title: breakfast casserole recipe
directions: Beat the above ingredients and pour over the sausage and cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: pumpkin-spice pie
directions: Whisk together all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie crust (9-inch). Bake at 350° until set in center and crust is golden, about 1 hour. Cool on rack in the refrigerator until cold.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: If making the night before, put cooked rice in bowl; mix in sugar and top with crushed pineapple and half of marshmallows. Cover tightly.

title: hot rolls for a crowd
directions: In a large bowl, soak milk, sugar and yeast for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add 4 cups flour, mixing well.
Let rise until "bubbly". Add eggs, salt, shortening and sugar; mix well, adding 6 cups of flour a little at a time.
Turn dough on floured surface.
Knead well; let rise until double and work down.
Make rolls; let rise and bake.
This recipe is good for cinnamon rolls.

title: prewash mix
directions: Mix equal parts of dishwashing liquid, ammonia and water in a spray bottle.
Be sure to label the bottle.
Spray on garment and wash immediately.
Do not let it set after spraying.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Heat butter and oil in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms.
Remove with slotted spoon; set aside.
Then add flour; form roux (gravy). Slowly add chicken broth; cook until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add cream, sherry, nutmeg and Parmesan cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add turkey and mushrooms.
Stir well.
Combine with cooked pasta.
Put into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs; sprinkle paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Mix according to directions on box.
(Note:
I use milk in place of water.)
Bake 20 minutes in jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Test.
If still wet, bake longer.
Set aside to cool.

title: grandma's homemade relish
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the vegetables and salt and let stand overnight.
Then rinse and drain the vegetable mixture. Next, combine the remaining ingredients together and pour over the vegetable mixture.
Place on stove and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes.
Then pour into hot pint size canning jars and seal.
Makes about 8 pint jars.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add sugar slowly.
Add vanilla while beating.
Mix nuts and crumbs.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: cranberry nut bread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil 2 large loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
In medium bowl, combine next 6 ingredients.
Using as few strokes as possible, stir liquid batter into dry batter, just until batters are combined.
Spread into pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap airtight.
May be frozen.

title: curry pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, salt and water stand for 5 hours.
Bring to
a boil
curry
powder,
vinegar,
sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over pickles and bring to a boil.
Then put into jar and seal.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, salt, turmeric and vinegar to rolling boil. Immediately pour over packed jars of cucumbers, garlic buds and dill.
You may add hot peppers, if you like hot dill pickles. Seal jars.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(You can use more or less pecans, cherries and coconut.)
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy low-fat pizza
directions: Place tortilla on cookie sheet.
If using pita pocket, simply place whole on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Use desired amount of sauce per pizza.
Layer your favorite veggies (chopped or sliced).
Follow with low-fat or nonfat cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit tea
directions: Brew tea in 2 cups water. Add sugar. Stir until dissolved. Add juices. Fill with water to make 1 gallon.

title: cheese topped spinach
directions: Place artichokes in greased 1-quart baking pan.
Drain spinach and spread over artichokes.
Blend cheese with butter, then mix in milk.
Spread cheese mixture over spinach.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Trim off the tops and roots of the leeks, discarding the tough outer layer.
Now, split them in half lengthwise and wash thoroughly under running water.
Slice them up quite finely.
Peel and dice potatoes and onions.

title: meal-in-a-pie casserole
directions: Pierce pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Mix brown gravy, meat, drained Veg-All and salt.
Pour into pie crust.
Mix together cheese, egg and milk.
Pour over meat mixture in crust. Bake 15 minutes at 400° or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the lettuce, cauliflower, mayonnaise and sugar mixture, onion, bacon and cheese.
Let set in layers overnight in refrigerator.
Mix and serve.

title: coconut surprise cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine sugar, shortening and 1/2 cup milk in mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat 10 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until layers test done.
Cool in pans for several minutes.
Remove from wire rack to cool completely.
Spread 7-Minute Frosting over 1 cake layer.
Arrange banana slices over frosting.
Add second layer of cake.
Spread 7-Minute Frosting over top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Yields 12 servings.

title: almond chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; brown in oil.
Place in baking dish. Combine soup, sherry, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Have small amount of grease in hot skillet.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in hot skillet; cook until golden brown at 400°.

title: tuna drops
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine flour, baking powder, onion, salt, curry powder and cayenne pepper.
Cut in margarine until mixture is size of small peas.
Add milk all at once and stir until well blended.
Add drained and flaked tuna, cheese, green pepper and olives; blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Yield:
36 servings.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 3 g, fat 3 g, calories 46.

title: meal in one
directions: Brown the
beef and drain.
Place layer of potatoes and onion in greased casserole dish.
Season with butter, salt and pepper. Add
layer
of
peas
and then layer of beef.
Repeat layers; pour soup
on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes (covered) and 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: cracker pie
directions: Crush crackers and add pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add vanilla.
Slowly add sugar and Karo; beat until stiff like divinity.
Pour crackers and nuts into egg white mixture and mix together.
Pour this into greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: citrus cheesecake
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°F.
Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press onto bottom and sides of a 13x9x2 pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: banana pudding
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; add to milk in double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks; cook until thick.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Pour over layers of bananas and vanilla wafers.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Beat in 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread on pudding. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs.
Add flour and milk, flour first and last.
Roll fruit and nuts in flour.
Pour batter over fruit and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: cinnamon-raisin bread(cooking light magazine)
directions: Dissolve 1/4 cup sugar and yeast in warm milk in a large bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and next 3 ingredients; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup raisins, stirring until a soft dough forms.

title: baked rigatoni and sausage
directions: Saute sausage in medium skillet until browned.
Remove from pan; slice into thin pieces.
Return to pan and add onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is tender, not brown.
Cook rigatoni for 10 minutes; drain.

title: spoon bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; stir.
Add flour, eggs, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate any dough left.

title: congealed cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water.
In a bowl combine pineapple, cottage cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Mix with gelatin and add broken pecans.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and dash of pepper; coat meat cubes in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot shortening in Dutch oven.
Add soup, 1 cup of water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and wine.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer.
Add peas and let sit, covered, about 15 minutes. Serve with buttered noodles.

title: scholotte point hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs (beaten), Shoe Peg corn and enough milk to make a medium-thick batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil until brown and done.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Drain the crushed pineapple and blend with the instant pudding.
Fold the Cool Whip into this mixture.
Fill between layers and on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut and pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Blend in vinegar.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: microwave cracker jacks
directions: Pour popped corn into grocery bag sprayed with Pam.
Cook brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt for 2 minutes on High.
Take out and stir.
Cook for 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda; stir until foamy.
Pour over the corn in the bag; stir well.
With corn still in the bag, cook for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake.
Cook for another 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake; cook 45 seconds. Pour onto cookie sheet, cool and break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain juice of cherries into measuring cup.
Add pineapple juice to make a full cup.
Add the brown sugar and tapioca.
Mix and pour over fruit in baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Stir 2 or 3 times.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry meat until brown.
As frying, add vegetables and seasoning.
As cooking, add water.
Add rice and water.
Cook on low heat and stir often.
Cook until rice is done.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut a slice from the top of pepper and discard seeds.
Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable spray.
Add ground meat.
Cook on medium heat until browned.
Put meat in colander and run under hot water to remove excess fat from meat. Set aside.

title: stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix and sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with milk to mixture.
Add eggs.
This makes a stiff batter.
Knead in additional flour to a cookie dough consistency.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Beat the shortening, boiling water and molasses together.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
(Batter is very soft.) Bake in 425° oven about 8 minutes.

title: 2 easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 package ham.
Form into a mound on a plate.
Press remaining 1 package ham around cheese ball (all over until covered with ham).

title: baked clams
directions: Heat sliced onion in the melted butter until onion turns yellow.

Add flour, clams, broth and cream. Simmer this for 20 minutes. Stir in the eggs and enough bread crumbs to thicken. Place the mixture in a greased casserole. Top with buttered crumbs and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until brown.

title: cherry chocolate banana dessert
directions: Spread half of the crumbs in a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Beat butter, powdered sugar and egg together until light and fluffy.
Spread over crumbs in pan.
Add maraschino cherries, banana and nuts, which have been mixed together.
Spread whipped cream over this mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over this. Chill 12 hours or longer.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and green chilies in butter until tender.
Add soup and broth, blending well.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
While sauce simmers, soften tortillas by dipping each in simmering mixture a few seconds.
Place a small amount of chicken on each tortilla and roll up tightly.
Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix eggs and milk together well.
Dip chops in egg and milk mixture.
Press in crackers.
Dip each pork chop in mixture twice; brown in skillet.
Place in roasting pan, cover and cook in a 300° oven for about 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until very thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar. Continue to beat until well blended.
Combine cold water, extract and rind. Add alternately in thirds with flour, sifted 3 times, to egg and sugar mixture. Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add baking powder and salt.
Continue beating until stiff.
Gently fold in the egg yolk mixture.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done. Invert pan 1 hour or until cake is cold.

title: quick casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger.
Drain and place on bottom of a large casserole dish.
Place potatoes on top of the meat.
Pour soup and meat on top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: vegetable and bread salad(fattoush)
directions: Mix vegetables and dressing.
Just before serving, add bread. Serves 4.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream ingredients.
Pour into deep crust pie tins.

title: gypsey's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni about 20 minutes and drain.
Grease casserole and then cover bottom with 1/2 of the shredded Cheddar cheese. Beat eggs; mix in milk and add macaroni.
Pour egg mixture over the shredded cheese in casserole.
Add balance of cheese, sprinkling on top, then spread a bit of butter on it.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken francese
directions: Flatten cutlets with meat pounder; dredge in flour, then into beaten eggs with parsley, black pepper and Parmesan.
Pan should be very hot.
Drop cutlets into oil and fry until golden.
Remove chicken; drain off oil.
Add sherry, lemon juice, chicken broth and chicken.
Cook 10 minutes uncovered until half of the liquid evaporates.
Add butter, additional parsley and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
If too moist, add a little flour.
Serve with a lemon slice on top.

title: company muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in sugar.
Add carrots, apples, raisins and nuts.
Make well in center; add oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: amish friendship starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add ingredients in a non-metal bowl and stir with a non-metal spoon until creamy.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand in a warm place for 2 days to ferment. It will become bubbly and have a sour odor.
Do not place in refrigerator.
On second day, third and fourth day, stir.
On the sixth, seventh, eighth and ninth day, stir.
On the fifth and tenth days, add 1 cup of each of flour, sugar and milk; stir. Reserve 1 cup of starter.
Pour remaining starter, 1 cup each, into 3 containers to give away to friends.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Pour flour into bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Cut in shortening.
